WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:03.544
[ LE TIGRE'S
"I'M SO EXCITED" PLAYS ]

00:03.544 --> 00:05.546
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

00:08.008 --> 00:10.051
OH,
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, SIR.

00:10.051 --> 00:11.432
[ LAUGHS ]
WELL, THANK YOU.

00:11.432 --> 00:13.844
UH, RICHARD,
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

00:13.844 --> 00:16.227
NOW, YOU'RE ONLY SAYING THAT
BECAUSE YOU HEARD HER SAY THAT.

00:16.227 --> 00:18.229
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
UH...GUILTY.

00:18.229 --> 00:19.770
[ CHUCKLES ] ACTUALLY,
CAN YOU COME AND FIND ME

00:19.770 --> 00:21.021
AT THE END OF YOUR DAY?

00:21.021 --> 00:23.064
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT YOUR SURGICAL SCHEDULE.

00:23.064 --> 00:25.066
OH, IS THAT RIGHT?

00:25.066 --> 00:26.067
YEAH. YEAH, IT IS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:26.067 --> 00:27.448
WELL...
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:27.448 --> 00:30.451
CATHERINE LET IT SLIP THAT
SHE WAS GONNA BE HERE TODAY,

00:30.451 --> 00:33.414
SO I'M ASSUMING THERE'S
SOME SORT OF SOMETHING.

00:33.414 --> 00:35.616
DON'T WORRY. DON'T WORRY.
I-I LIKE SURPRISES.

00:35.616 --> 00:38.369
I'M SORRY, BUT...IT IS ACTUALLY
ABOUT YOUR SURGICAL SCHEDULE.

00:38.369 --> 00:41.582
BAILEY,
YOU CAN'T LIE TO ME.
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

00:41.582 --> 00:44.004
WAIT -- I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT ANY PARTY.

00:44.004 --> 00:46.217
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, THOUGH.
HMM.

00:46.217 --> 00:48.839
♪ I'LL LET IT GO ♪
OH, OH, I DO HAVE SOMETHING
FOR YOU, THOUGH.

00:48.839 --> 00:51.051
♪ I'M SO EXCITED ♪
OWEN, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

00:51.051 --> 00:52.843
♪ I JUST CAN'T HIDE IT ♪
I DIDN'T.
IT'S FROM THE HOSPITAL.

00:52.843 --> 00:55.055
UH, MAKE SURE YOU COME AND
SEE ME AT THE END OF THE DAY.

00:55.055 --> 00:57.228
♪ I'M ABOUT TO LOSE CONTROL,
AND I THINK I LIKE IT ♪

00:57.228 --> 00:58.479
YEAH.

00:58.479 --> 01:02.183
♪ I'M SO EXCITED ♪

01:02.183 --> 01:05.186
♪ I JUST CAN'T HIDE IT ♪

01:05.186 --> 01:07.027
THAT WOULD BE GREAT.
♪ I KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW ♪

01:07.027 --> 01:08.319
Meredith: THERE'S A STAGE YOU
GO THROUGH DURING CHILDBIRTH.

01:08.319 --> 01:10.951
♪ I WANT TO, I WANT TO ♪
AND IT'S THE TOUGHEST PART.

01:10.951 --> 01:13.154
IT'S CALLED
THE TRANSITION STAGE.
♪ I'M SO EXCITED ♪

01:13.154 --> 01:14.745
HEY, HAPPY BIRTHDAY!
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

01:14.745 --> 01:16.867
♪ I JUST CAN'T HIDE IT ♪
THAT'S GREAT.

01:16.867 --> 01:17.998
IT WAS.

01:17.998 --> 01:19.540
YOU'VE BEEN PUSHING
SO HARD AND SO LONG...

01:19.540 --> 01:21.081
♪ I KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW ♪

01:21.081 --> 01:23.874
♪ I WANT TO, I WANT TO ♪
...YOU'RE EXHAUSTED, SPENT.

01:23.874 --> 01:27.007
AND THERE'S NOTHING TO SHOW
FOR ALL OF YOUR EFFORT.

01:27.007 --> 01:29.420
OH, MY GOD! THERE SHE IS!
OKAY, WELL,
SHE'S NOT A SHE.

01:29.420 --> 01:31.302
SHE'S AN IT, AND SHE'S FRAGILE,
SO DON'T TOUCH IT.

01:31.302 --> 01:33.844
SORRY, I'M JUST,
UH, EXTREMELY EXCITED.

01:33.844 --> 01:35.886
WELL, YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE
PRINTING ANYTHING JUST YET.

01:35.886 --> 01:37.218
ISN'T THAT THE JOB?
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:37.218 --> 01:39.059
I -- YOU HIRED ME
TO HELP RE-ENGINEER

01:39.059 --> 01:40.221
YOUR --
YOUR PORTAL VEINS.

01:40.221 --> 01:42.853
I BEAT OUT 100 BIOENGINEERS
FOR THE GIG.

01:42.853 --> 01:45.186
I'VE, UH, COOKED UP
A COUPLE OF DESIGNS.

01:45.186 --> 01:47.528
OH, THAT'S AWESOME.
NO, ACTUALLY
IT'S PRESUMPTUOUS.

01:47.528 --> 01:49.730
UNTIL YOU'VE READ
EVERY SCRAP OF DATA

01:49.730 --> 01:51.402
ON EVERY TEST WE'VE RUN,
YOU TOUCH NOTHING.

01:51.402 --> 01:53.444
THERE ARE
THE RESEARCH BINDERS,

01:53.444 --> 01:55.946
SO YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
JUST GO AHEAD AND DIG IN.

01:55.946 --> 01:57.828
GREAT. CAN I, UH,
TOUCH THE CHAIR?

01:58.699 --> 02:00.000
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:03.334 --> 02:06.126
KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.
HE TOUCHES NOTHING.

02:06.126 --> 02:08.959
DO YOU WANT ME
TO WATCH HIM READ?
YES!

02:08.959 --> 02:11.552
DURING THIS TRANSITION STAGE,
IT FEELS LIKE YOU CAN'T GO ON.

02:11.552 --> 02:14.134
[ DOOR OPENS ]
BUT IT'S ONLY BECAUSE
YOU'RE VERY NEARLY THERE.

02:14.134 --> 02:16.056
[ SIGHS ]

02:16.056 --> 02:19.059
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

02:23.143 --> 02:25.145
YOUR SON
IS 4 YEARS OLD?

02:25.145 --> 02:27.027
4, YES.

02:27.027 --> 02:28.859
AND HE'S HAD
TWO PREVIOUS CONDUIT FAILURES.

02:28.859 --> 02:30.691
Man: BUT YOUR CONDUIT
WORKS, RIGHT?

02:30.691 --> 02:32.323
FROM WHAT WE READ,
BABY NATHAN IS DOING GREAT.

02:32.323 --> 02:35.155
YES. IT WAS SUCCESSFUL
IN NATHAN'S CASE.

02:35.155 --> 02:36.827
THIS CLINICAL TRIAL

02:36.827 --> 02:39.039
IS TO IDENTIFY CERTAIN ASPECTS
OF THE PROCEDURE.

02:39.039 --> 02:40.120
BUT HE'LL GET THE CONDUIT?

02:40.120 --> 02:43.123
IF YOU'RE CHOSEN
FOR THE STUDY.

02:43.123 --> 02:44.955
DR. YANG
HAS THE FINAL SAY,

02:44.955 --> 02:46.747
AND I'M FORWARDING
YOUR MATERIALS ON TO HER.

02:46.747 --> 02:47.918
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

02:47.918 --> 02:49.500
OOH.
[ RECORDER BEEPS ]

02:49.500 --> 02:51.131
NUMBER 14 LOOKS GOOD --

02:51.131 --> 02:55.055
SOME EC-TCPC NARROWING
WITH EARLY SIGNS OF OBSTRUCTION.

02:55.055 --> 02:56.847
THERE IS EVIDENCE OF --
HEY.

02:56.847 --> 02:58.849
YOU, UH, PICKING
RESEARCH SUBJECTS TODAY?

02:58.849 --> 03:00.511
HOW'S IT GOING?
UH, GOOD.

03:00.511 --> 03:01.932
SHANE'S MEETING
WITH THE CANDIDATES.
[ RECORDER BEEPS ]

03:01.932 --> 03:03.724
I'M ONLY LOOKING
AT THE HEARTS --

03:03.724 --> 03:06.146
TRYING TO KEEP
MY JUDGMENT UNSULLIED.

03:06.146 --> 03:08.108
BUT IT'S HARD FINDING CANDIDATES
THAT MEET ALL THE CRITERIA.

03:08.108 --> 03:09.440
YEAH.

03:09.440 --> 03:11.482
YOU NEED THIS.

03:11.482 --> 03:14.485
WHAT? A...HYPOPLASTIC
LEFT VENTRICLE?

03:14.485 --> 03:16.277
NO, LIKE AN ALGORITHM --

03:16.277 --> 03:19.700
SOME SCIENTIFIC WAY
OF CHOOSING THE PERFECT MATE

03:19.700 --> 03:22.493
WHERE YOU INPUT
ONLY THE CRITERIA YOU WANT,

03:22.493 --> 03:25.376
AND YOU'RE PRESENTED
WITH ONLY SUITABLE CANDIDATES.

03:25.376 --> 03:26.707
SO, INTERNET DATING.

03:26.707 --> 03:28.499
OH, RIGHT.
THEY HAVE THAT.

03:28.499 --> 03:31.292
LISTEN, I DON'T
NEED A DATE. OKAY?

03:31.292 --> 03:34.715
OH, UH, KEEP ME POSTED
ON THE HEARTS.

03:37.548 --> 03:39.340
HOW LONG DOES IT TAKE
TO WASH ONE, LIKE 10 SECONDS?

03:39.340 --> 03:40.971
LOOK, I DON'T LIKE
A FILTHY KITCHEN, EITHER.

03:40.971 --> 03:42.142
DIRTY CEREAL BOWLS
IN THE SINK

03:42.142 --> 03:43.764
AREN'T GONNA
EXACTLY TIP THE SCALES.

03:43.764 --> 03:45.556
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
[ Sighing ] OH, MY JESUS.

03:45.556 --> 03:46.767
WELL, NOW THAT
HE'S IN THE CONVERSATION,

03:46.767 --> 03:47.938
I'LL MAKE SURE
TO CLEAN THE BOWLS TONIGHT.

03:47.938 --> 03:49.189
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
YOUR MOTHER. YOUR MOTHER.

03:51.402 --> 03:55.155
OH. UM...

03:55.155 --> 03:57.358
SHE DOES
NOT LOOK HAPPY.

03:57.358 --> 03:58.949
COME ON.
IT'LL -- IT'LL BE FINE.

03:58.949 --> 04:00.200
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT.

04:00.200 --> 04:01.412
BUT Y-Y-YOU TOLD HER,
RIGHT?

04:01.412 --> 04:02.663
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
HER? I DID.

04:02.663 --> 04:04.825
HOW DID SHE TAKE IT?
HMM?

04:04.825 --> 04:06.417
SO...

04:07.668 --> 04:12.373
...I UNDERSTAND
CONGRATULATIONS ARE IN ORDER.

04:12.373 --> 04:13.504
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

04:13.504 --> 04:16.216
[ SIGHS ]

04:16.216 --> 04:19.089
AND HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN
EXPERIENCING THIS PAIN, GREG?

04:19.089 --> 04:20.050
YOU KNOW,
COMES AND GOES.

04:20.050 --> 04:22.262
10 YEARS.
10 YEARS?

04:22.262 --> 04:23.474
MM-HMM,
SINCE WE'VE BEEN MARRIED.

04:23.474 --> 04:25.476
HE WON'T GO SEE ANYONE.
I JUST GOT OBAMACARE.

04:25.476 --> 04:26.887
I'M A JUNK COLLECTOR.

04:26.887 --> 04:29.730
I S-SELL STUFF
AT FLEA MARKETS.

04:29.730 --> 04:31.151
DOESN'T REALLY MAKE
FOR REGULAR COVERAGE.

04:31.151 --> 04:33.153
OH, THERE'S DEFINITELY
A MASS HERE.

04:33.153 --> 04:34.895
OH, IT'S CANCER.

04:34.895 --> 04:35.856
IS IT CANCER?
JODI.

04:35.856 --> 04:38.068
[ GASPS ]
WHAT?

04:38.068 --> 04:39.400
OH, NOTHING.

04:39.400 --> 04:41.992
NOTHING.
UH, COULD BE MINOR.

04:41.992 --> 04:45.035
WE'LL KNOW MORE
WHEN WE GET A C.T.

04:45.035 --> 04:46.827
SEE? I KNEW WE SHOULD HAVE
COME IN EARLIER.

04:46.827 --> 04:47.998
WHAT DID YOU SEE?
WAS IT BAD?

04:47.998 --> 04:49.370
IF IT WAS BAD,
WHY DO YOU LOOK SO HAPPY?

04:49.370 --> 04:53.123
JUST GET HIM TO C.T. AND SPEAK
TO NO ONE OF THIS -- NO ONE!

04:53.123 --> 04:55.085
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

04:55.085 --> 04:56.917
[ DOOR OPENS ]

04:56.917 --> 04:59.129
YOU PAGED ME?
HEY, CALLIE.

04:59.129 --> 05:00.421
WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY SURGERY?

05:00.421 --> 05:02.633
I WAS SUPPOSED TO REMOVE
THE SENSORS ON WILL MITCHELL,

05:02.633 --> 05:04.475
AND, UH, I FOUND OUT
MY SURGERY WAS CANCELED.

05:04.475 --> 05:06.056
YEAH, THAT'S WHY
I PAGED YOU.

05:06.056 --> 05:08.228
UH, DR. TORRES CAME TO ME
WITH A CONCERN

05:08.228 --> 05:11.061
ABOUT AN INTELLECTUAL-PROPERTY
CONFLICT BETWEEN YOU TWO.

05:11.061 --> 05:12.102
WHAT, IS THIS
ABOUT THE SENSORS?

05:12.102 --> 05:14.525
YES, DEREK.
IT'S ABOUT OUR SENSORS.

05:14.525 --> 05:16.316
LOOK,
L-L-LET'S JUST TALK.

05:16.316 --> 05:17.488
I'M SURE
WE CAN FIND A SOLUTION.

05:17.488 --> 05:19.700
WHO'S THIS?
OH, THAT'S PAULA.

05:19.700 --> 05:21.151
SHE'S MY LAWYER.

05:22.863 --> 05:26.036
[ SIGHS ] IS IT?

05:26.036 --> 05:28.709
IS IT?

05:28.709 --> 05:31.372
[ GASPS ] IT IS!

05:31.372 --> 05:32.793
WHAT?

05:32.793 --> 05:34.164
[ Laughing ]
LOOK AT IT, MURPHY.

05:34.164 --> 05:35.586
IT'S GLORIOUS.

05:35.586 --> 05:36.797
IT'S A MASS.

05:36.797 --> 05:38.719
I-IT'S A MASSIVE MASS,
BUT --

05:38.719 --> 05:41.131
OH, MY GOD.

05:41.131 --> 05:43.464
AAH! [ LAUGHS ]

05:43.464 --> 05:47.057
OKAY, SO, WE'RE GONNA NEED
A 3-D RECONSTRUCTION AND, UM --

05:47.057 --> 05:49.470
HEY, DR. BAILEY. HEY, DO YOU
HAVE THE LABS ON THE -- UM...

05:49.470 --> 05:50.681
I SAID, "TELL NO ONE"!
I DIDN'T!

05:50.681 --> 05:52.272
TELL NO ONE WHAT?

05:52.272 --> 05:53.604
IS THAT A --

05:53.604 --> 05:56.106
YEAH! OKAY,
KEEP YOUR VOICE DOWN.

05:56.106 --> 05:58.188
I WANT IN.
D-- NO! IT'S MINE.

05:58.188 --> 05:59.149
IT'S OURS.

05:59.149 --> 06:01.191
PAGE DR. WEBBER.
WHY HIM?

06:01.191 --> 06:03.153
IT'S HIS BIRTHDAY.

06:03.153 --> 06:04.985
I'LL BE FORWARDING YOUR
MATERIALS ON TO DR. YANG.

06:04.985 --> 06:06.156
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.
WE'LL LET YOU KNOW.

06:06.156 --> 06:08.368
OH. SORRY.

06:08.368 --> 06:10.751
HI. I'M HERE
FOR THE HLHS TRIAL.

06:10.751 --> 06:11.952
YES, AND YOU ARE --

06:11.952 --> 06:13.163
SHERYLL JEFFRIES.

06:13.163 --> 06:14.334
OH, NO,
I'M NOT ON THE LIST.

06:14.334 --> 06:17.337
THAT STUPID NURSE OF WHATEVER
SHE WAS SAID I DIDN'T QUALIFY.

06:17.337 --> 06:19.339
I'M WHAT
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

06:19.339 --> 06:22.342
HLHS WITH AT LEAST ONE
FAILED CONDUIT PROCEDURE.

06:22.342 --> 06:23.634
THAT'S ME.

06:23.634 --> 06:25.636
AH. I'M...SORRY,
SHERYLL.

06:25.636 --> 06:28.178
THE STUDY IS
FOR PEDIATRIC PATIENTS OVER 1.

06:28.178 --> 06:29.680
I'M 17.
I AM A PEDIATRIC PATIENT.

06:29.680 --> 06:32.272
WE'RE LOOKING FOR
PRE-PUBESCENT SPECIFICALLY --

06:32.272 --> 06:34.064
KIDS THAT
ARE STILL GROWING.

06:34.064 --> 06:35.065
THAT'S PERFECT.

06:35.065 --> 06:36.396
I JUST HAD
A HUGE GROWTH SPURT.
[ SIGHS ]

06:36.396 --> 06:38.188
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
SINCE I GOT KNOCKED UP

06:38.188 --> 06:40.481
SOMEONE SAID
I'M TOO OLD FOR SOMETHING.

06:40.481 --> 06:43.073
LOOK,
I'M DUE IN SIX WEEKS.

06:43.073 --> 06:44.985
I WANT A HEART
THAT'S GONNA SURVIVE IT, OKAY?

06:44.985 --> 06:47.197
AND WHY DO YOU NEED ME
TO LOOK AT IT?

06:47.197 --> 06:48.619
IT'S FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY.

06:48.619 --> 06:50.951
NO MORE TALK
ABOUT MY BIRTHDAY.

06:50.951 --> 06:54.164
I MEAN, THERE ARE FINE SURGEONS
WORKING WELL INTO THEIR 70s,

06:54.164 --> 06:55.035
AND I AM NOWHERE NEAR 70.

06:55.035 --> 06:58.378
WILL YOU JUST LOOK
AT THE MONITOR.

07:00.671 --> 07:03.043
[ Muttering ] MONITOR.

07:03.043 --> 07:05.466
LET'S SEE. OKAY. WELL...

07:05.466 --> 07:07.217
OH, MY WORD.

07:07.217 --> 07:10.050
I-I-IS THAT
A LITTLE LEG?

07:10.050 --> 07:11.762
AND A SPINAL COLUMN.

07:11.762 --> 07:13.053
IT IS.

07:13.053 --> 07:16.056
IT'S A FETUS IN FETU.

07:16.056 --> 07:17.057
IT IS.

07:17.057 --> 07:18.479
THE MAN ABSORBED
HIS OWN TWIN.

07:18.479 --> 07:20.731
[ Chuckling ] HE DID.

07:20.731 --> 07:22.152
YOU KNOW, IN ALL MY YEARS,
I'VE NEVER SEEN ONE.

07:22.152 --> 07:23.153
NEITHER HAVE I!
NEITHER HAVE I!

07:23.153 --> 07:24.114
[ LAUGHS ] WELL...

07:24.114 --> 07:25.195
[ RAPS TABLE ]
HOT DIGGITY!

07:25.195 --> 07:28.028
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

07:28.028 --> 07:31.031
AH, LOOK AT THAT.
OH, MY.

07:41.542 --> 07:42.753
A LOVE CONTRACT?

07:42.753 --> 07:44.464
WHERE DID GREY GET THIS,
ZOLA'S BARBIE DREAM HOUSE?

07:44.464 --> 07:45.846
[ SIGHS ] NO.
IT'S A REAL THING. I SWEAR.

07:45.846 --> 07:47.177
[ SIGHS ]

07:47.177 --> 07:50.390
"WE CONFIRM THAT ANY SEXUAL
AND/OR ROMANTIC RELATIONSHIP

07:50.390 --> 07:52.392
IS COMPLETELY VOLUNTARY."

07:52.392 --> 07:54.394
THIS IS SO CREEPY --

07:54.394 --> 07:56.647
LIKE WE HAVE TO VOW
TO THE HOSPITAL GODS?

07:56.647 --> 07:58.519
HEY, ALEX, WE HAVE
A TRANSORAL FUNDOPLICATION.

07:58.519 --> 07:59.650
I SENT YOU THE LATEST LABS.
Jo: WHAT'S THAT?

07:59.650 --> 08:01.732
OH, IT'S REALLY,
REALLY COOL.

08:01.732 --> 08:02.603
FIRST, WE GO IN ORALLY,

08:02.603 --> 08:03.734
AND THEN WE GO IN
THROUGH THE BELLY BUTTON

08:03.734 --> 08:06.486
TO FIX A KID'S REFLUX
WITHOUT LEAVING A SCAR.

08:06.486 --> 08:07.868
IT PUTS THE "FUN"
IN "FUNDOPLICATION."

08:07.868 --> 08:09.239
GOD,
THAT DOES SOUND FUN.

08:09.239 --> 08:10.531
YEAH.
SEE?
YOU COULD GET ON THAT.

08:10.531 --> 08:12.322
JUST SIGN THAT,
AND YOU COULD BE BACK ON PEDS.

08:12.322 --> 08:14.114
YEAH,
I'M NOT SIGNING THAT.

08:14.114 --> 08:17.748
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:17.748 --> 08:18.959
Greg: I HAVE A TWIN?

08:18.959 --> 08:21.171
YOU DID -- IN UTERO.

08:21.171 --> 08:22.543
OH, GROSS.
HE ATE HIS TWIN?

08:22.543 --> 08:23.544
ABSORBED IT?

08:23.544 --> 08:25.125
OR RATHER ENVELOPED IT.

08:25.125 --> 08:26.837
GREG,
YOU DEVELOPED AROUND IT.

08:26.837 --> 08:28.839
OH, WOW. OH, WOW.
OH, I'M GONNA NEED A MINUTE.

08:28.839 --> 08:31.301
IS IT DANGEROUS?
I MEAN, CAN IT KILL HIM?

08:31.301 --> 08:33.183
JODI.
NO. IN -- IN MANY CASES,
IT'S HARMLESS,

08:33.183 --> 08:35.345
BUT GREG'S IS THE SOURCE
OF HIS PAIN,

08:35.345 --> 08:38.348
SO THAT LIKELY INDICATES
THAT IT WILL

08:38.348 --> 08:40.561
CAUSE PROBLEMS
IF IT HASN'T ALREADY.

08:40.561 --> 08:41.772
GOOD NEWS --
WE WERE ABLE TO

08:41.772 --> 08:43.353
SCHEDULE SURGERY TODAY
TO REMOVE IT.

08:43.353 --> 08:44.735
STOP CALLING HIM "IT"!

08:44.735 --> 08:46.486
EVERYONE
NEEDS TO SLOW DOWN.

08:46.486 --> 08:48.528
I JUST FOUND OUT
I HAVE A BROTHER.

08:51.531 --> 08:52.703
I'M SORRY, SHERYLL.

08:52.703 --> 08:53.954
I WISH I COULD HELP YOU,
BUT RULES ARE RULES.

08:53.954 --> 08:55.826
JUST BEND THEM, OKAY?

08:55.826 --> 08:57.708
I CAN'T.
[ SIGHS ]

08:57.708 --> 08:59.159
SHERYLL, PLEASE,
IF I COULD --

08:59.159 --> 09:01.752
MY WATER BROKE.
I THINK.

09:01.752 --> 09:03.213
OH, BOY

09:03.213 --> 09:05.425
I NEED A WHEELCHAIR HERE!
Woman: I'LL GET ONE.

09:05.425 --> 09:06.797
AND PAGE
LABOR AND DELIVERY!
RIGHT AWAY.

09:06.797 --> 09:09.429
CAN I CALL THE BABY'S FATHER,
YOUR PARENTS?

09:09.429 --> 09:10.591
MY PARENTS
DON'T TALK TO ME.

09:10.591 --> 09:12.052
NOT SURE
WHO THE FATHER IS --

09:12.052 --> 09:13.383
PROBABLY WHY MY PARENTS
DON'T TALK TO ME.

09:13.383 --> 09:16.346
[ GRUNTS ] THE PERSON
YOU CAN CALL IS DR. YANG.

09:16.346 --> 09:18.769
AND TELL HER
TO MAKE AN EXCEPTION.

09:18.769 --> 09:20.480
Cristina: SHE'S TOO OLD.

09:20.480 --> 09:22.272
YOU NEED A REFRESHER
ON WHEN PUBERTY BEGINS, ROSS?

09:22.272 --> 09:24.645
I KNOW. I JUST...
THOUGHT WE COULD BEND THE RULES.

09:24.645 --> 09:26.607
AND SKEW THE RESULTS
OF THE TRIAL.

09:26.607 --> 09:27.948
NO, BUT THIS PATIENT --
I TOLD YOU.

09:27.948 --> 09:31.531
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW ABOUT THE
PATIENT SO I'M NOT INFLUENCED.

09:31.531 --> 09:34.745
I ONLY WANT TO SEE THE HEART --
A HEART THAT HAS HAD

09:34.745 --> 09:37.407
A PREVIOUS SURGERY
TO CORRECT THE DEFECT,

09:37.407 --> 09:39.620
IS CURRENTLY
IN POOR CARDIAC HEALTH,

09:39.620 --> 09:42.623
AND IS IN THE BODY OF A KID
BETWEEN THE AGES OF 1 AND 12.

09:42.623 --> 09:45.626
A HEART THAT IS STILL GROWING --
IS THIS THAT HEART?

09:47.587 --> 09:50.590
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

09:50.590 --> 09:52.803
HEY.

09:52.803 --> 09:54.765
SO, I WAS THINKING ABOUT THIS
WHOLE INTERNET-DATING THING.

09:54.765 --> 09:56.767
It takes five minutes.
WAIT. THAT'S WHY
YOU PAGED ME?

09:56.767 --> 09:58.178
YOU SAID THIS WAS URGENT.

09:58.178 --> 10:00.931
It is. I'm about to get busy
with this trial.

10:00.931 --> 10:04.775
AND YOU NEED SOMEONE TO SNUGGLE
WITH ON RAINY SEATTLE NIGHTS.

10:04.775 --> 10:06.566
OOH.
SAY THAT IN YOU PROFILE.

10:06.566 --> 10:07.858
I-I, UH -- I GOT TO GO.
I GOT TO GO.

10:07.858 --> 10:09.690
CALLIE, THIS IS NOT SOMETHING
I'M DOING TO YOU.

10:09.690 --> 10:10.821
I HAVE A SIGNED CONTRACT
WITH THEM.

10:10.821 --> 10:12.112
YEAH, THAT YOU HAD
NO RIGHT TO SIGN.

10:12.112 --> 10:14.154
YOU SIGNED AWAY
SOMETHING THAT'S OURS.

10:14.154 --> 10:15.736
COME ON. WE SPENT HALF THE DAY
TOGETHER YESTERDAY.

10:15.736 --> 10:17.157
WE WERE ON A PLAYDATE.
WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAY SOMETHING THEN?

10:17.157 --> 10:18.578
WE WERE WITH THE KIDS.
OH, WE HAVE
SOPHIA'S DRESSY DOLL.

10:18.578 --> 10:19.950
I THINK ZOLA THOUGHT
IT WAS HERS.

10:19.950 --> 10:21.371
HA.
WHAT?

10:21.371 --> 10:22.542
OH, LIKE FATHER,
LIKE DAUGHTER, I GUESS.

10:22.542 --> 10:24.544
Owen: I THINK WE'RE -- WE'RE --
WE'RE DRIFTING HERE.

10:24.544 --> 10:25.746
[ SIGHS ] YES, YES,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

10:25.746 --> 10:26.707
I'M SORRY.
THAT WAS UNPROFESSIONAL.

10:26.707 --> 10:28.709
WHAT I SHOULD HAVE SAID
WAS...

10:28.709 --> 10:30.921
"THE SENSORS ARE MATERIALS
THAT YOU CO-DEVELOPED WITH ME

10:30.921 --> 10:33.013
"IN SERVICE
OF RESEARCH I STARTED

10:33.013 --> 10:34.805
AND INVITED YOU
TO PARTICIPATE IN."

10:34.805 --> 10:37.017
IF YOU ATTEMPT TO IMPAIR
MY ACCESS TO THESE MATERIALS,

10:37.017 --> 10:39.179
I WILL HAVE YOU PROSECUTED TO
THE FULLEST EXTENT OF THE LAW.

10:39.179 --> 10:41.762
WELL SAID.
THIS IS INSANE.

10:41.762 --> 10:43.643
YOU DON'T HAVE A CASE.

10:43.643 --> 10:45.686
LISTEN, BEFORE ANYONE
RESORTS TO LITIGATION,

10:45.686 --> 10:47.858
LET ME JUST TAKE THIS
BEFORE THE OTHER BOARD MEMBERS.

10:47.858 --> 10:51.531
MAYBE WE CAN FIND A SOLUTION
THAT IS FAIR TO BOTH PARTIES.

10:51.531 --> 10:54.654
IN THE MEANTIME, I WANT YOU BOTH
TO LEAVE THIS MATTER ALONE

10:54.654 --> 10:55.906
UNTIL YOU HEAR FROM ME?

10:55.906 --> 10:57.407
[ SIGHS ]
ALL RIGHT?

10:59.119 --> 11:01.161
I'M SURE IT WAS A SHOCK.
I MEAN, I WAS SHOCKED.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.123
I CAN'T EVEN IMAGINE
WHAT YOU MUST BE FEELING.

11:03.123 --> 11:05.045
ACTUALLY, I CAN.
I CAN IMAGINE IT BECAUSE I --

11:05.045 --> 11:06.877
YOU KNOW WHAT? BABE, DON'T.
SHE DOESN'T CARE.

11:06.877 --> 11:08.668
BUT I KNOW
WHY YOU'RE HERE, MOM,

11:08.668 --> 11:10.290
AND I COULD HAVE
SAVED YOU A TRIP.

11:10.290 --> 11:11.501
I ALREADY CALLED
MIKE FARRIS.

11:11.501 --> 11:13.093
THE TIME TO CALL MIKE
WOULD HAVE BEEN

11:13.093 --> 11:15.716
BEFORE YOU STOOD UP
AT THAT...BARN.

11:15.716 --> 11:16.967
WAIT,
WHO IS MIKE HARRIS?

11:16.967 --> 11:18.759
"FARRIS" -- HE'S OUR ATTORNEY.
AVERY FOUNDATION.

11:18.759 --> 11:20.801
PROTECTS
OUR FINANCIAL INTERESTS.

11:20.801 --> 11:25.015
UM, ARE YOU SUGGESTING
THAT I'M AFTER YOUR MONEY?

11:25.015 --> 11:27.437
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE AFTER, DEAR.

11:27.437 --> 11:28.729
ALL RIGHT,
THAT'S ENOUGH.

11:28.729 --> 11:30.020
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
MARCH IN HERE

11:30.020 --> 11:31.982
AND START QUESTIONING
MY WIFE'S CHARACTER.

11:31.982 --> 11:33.814
YOU WANT TO TALK
ABOUT HER CHARACTER?

11:33.814 --> 11:35.275
SHE LEFT A MAN AT THE ALTAR.

11:35.275 --> 11:37.868
SHE BROKE HIS HEART
AND HUMILIATED HIM

11:37.868 --> 11:40.280
IN FRONT OF EVERYONE
THAT HE LOVES.

11:40.280 --> 11:42.873
I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT SHE'S
CAPABLE OF, NEVER MIND YOU.

11:42.873 --> 11:45.085
I AM NOT INTERESTED
IN YOUR MONEY.

11:45.085 --> 11:46.536
WONDERFUL.

11:46.536 --> 11:48.628
THAT'S WHAT I SAID WHEN
I MARRIED INTO THE AVERY FAMILY,

11:48.628 --> 11:49.669
AND YOU KNOW
WHAT I DID NEXT?

11:49.669 --> 11:51.711
I SIGNED
A PRENUPTIAL AGREEMENT.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.673
I SAID I'D HANDLE IT.
THIS IS TOTALLY INAPPROPRIATE.

11:53.673 --> 11:56.546
WHAT'S INAPPROPRIATE
IS THE ENGAGEMENT

11:56.546 --> 11:59.389
WAS 15 MINUTES AT A REST STOP
ON THE TURNPIKE.

11:59.389 --> 12:01.721
FORTUNATELY,
POSTNUPTIAL AGREEMENTS

12:01.721 --> 12:04.304
WERE CREATED
FOR MOMENTS LIKE THIS.

12:04.304 --> 12:06.556
AND THIS MEETING IS OVER.
[ SCOFFS ]

12:06.556 --> 12:07.557
JACKSON.
IT'S OVER!

12:07.557 --> 12:09.349
LOOK AT THIS. I --

12:19.529 --> 12:20.740
I'LL SIGN
THE STUPID PAPER.

12:20.740 --> 12:21.741
REALLY -- I DON'T MIND.

12:21.741 --> 12:22.863
YOU'RE NOT SIGNING
ANYTHING.

12:22.863 --> 12:24.204
WHY NOT?
I DON'T WANT YOUR MONEY.

12:24.204 --> 12:25.205
I WANT YOU.

12:25.205 --> 12:26.576
A PRENUP OR WHATEVER
THE HELL IT IS

12:26.576 --> 12:27.747
IS ONLY FOR IF WE GET DIVORCED,
WHICH WE'RE NOT GONNA DO,

12:27.747 --> 12:28.959
SO IT DOESN'T MATTER.

12:28.959 --> 12:30.540
APRIL, THAT IS NOT
THE POINT, OKAY?

12:30.540 --> 12:33.083
THIS IS A CONVERSATION
FOR YOU AND I WHEN WE ARE READY,

12:33.083 --> 12:35.255
NOT FOR HER TO COME
BARGING IN DICTATING TERMS.

12:35.255 --> 12:36.426
BUT IT WILL CALM HER DOWN.

12:36.426 --> 12:38.048
I'M PART
OF HER FAMILY NOW.

12:38.048 --> 12:39.549
I DON'T THINK
AN OLIVE BRANCH

12:39.549 --> 12:40.801
IS THE WORST THING
IN THE WORLD TO OFFER.

12:40.801 --> 12:42.592
YEAH, WELL, YOU'RE
A BETTER PERSON THAN I AM.

12:42.592 --> 12:44.014
WELL, YES.

12:44.014 --> 12:45.475
AND THAN SHE IS.

12:45.475 --> 12:46.646
I'M BETTER
THAN EVERYONE.

12:46.646 --> 12:48.648
[ SIGHS ]

12:48.648 --> 12:50.650
MNH-MNH.
NOT RIGHT NOW.

12:50.650 --> 12:53.984
WE CAN LET HER STEW
FOR A WHILE.

12:53.984 --> 12:55.395
[ GASPS ]
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

12:55.395 --> 12:56.776
LE-- I -- COME ON.

12:56.776 --> 12:57.988
[ LAUGHS ]
I HATE YOU.

12:57.988 --> 12:59.779
I KNOW, RIGHT?
DO YOU WANT TO SEE?

12:59.779 --> 13:03.203
NO. I WANT TO WORK
ON THAT PRINTER.

13:03.203 --> 13:05.035
AND IT MY JOB
TO MAKE SURE HE DOESN'T.

13:05.035 --> 13:06.406
SERIOUSLY?
YEAH. DON'T...

13:06.406 --> 13:09.789
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE DOING
INSTEAD OF THIS.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.671
OH, COME ON!

13:11.671 --> 13:13.874
ALL RIGHT.
WHAT IS THAT?
OKAY.

13:13.874 --> 13:16.506
HAVE YOU EVER, EVER
SEEN ANYTHING LIKE THIS?

13:16.506 --> 13:17.878
OH, HOLY GOD!

13:17.878 --> 13:19.880
NO, I NEVER WANTED TO!
WHAT IS THAT?

13:19.880 --> 13:21.631
IT'S A FETUS IN A FETUS.

13:21.631 --> 13:23.013
THAT I AM DOWN HERE
NOT SEEING.

13:23.013 --> 13:24.594
I CAN TOTALLY READ
WITHOUT SUPERVISION --

13:24.594 --> 13:26.136
BEEN DOING IT FOR YEARS.
THAT'S NOT READING.

13:26.136 --> 13:28.268
THAT'S DOODLING. READ.

13:28.268 --> 13:29.559
WELL [SIGHS]
THIS HAS BEEN FUN,

13:29.559 --> 13:32.142
BUT I HAVE TO TAKE A MAN
OUT OF A MAN.

13:32.142 --> 13:33.813
WANT ANOTHER PEAK?
I'M GOOD ACTUALLY.

13:36.066 --> 13:38.648
THAT --
HOW WOULD IT WORK?

13:38.648 --> 13:39.819
THEORETICALLY.

13:42.282 --> 13:43.864
LET'S GO.
KEEP IT MOVING, PEOPLE.

13:43.864 --> 13:46.406
EVERYBODY NEEDS TO TAKE A LOOK
BECAUSE THIS, MY FRIENDS,

13:46.406 --> 13:50.040
IS THE HALLEY'S COMET
OF YOUR CAREERS,

13:50.040 --> 13:54.915
AS RARE, WONDROUS,
A-A-AND FLEETING -- DR. HUNT.

13:54.915 --> 13:56.546
CAN I HELP YOU
WITH SOMETHING?

13:56.546 --> 13:58.418
Owen: YEAH, I JUST CAME
TO HAVE A LOOK.

13:58.418 --> 14:00.090
YOU KNOW
THERE'S A LINE.

14:00.090 --> 14:02.883
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'RE --

14:02.883 --> 14:04.094
YOU'RE SERIOUS?

14:04.094 --> 14:06.967
[ SCOFFS ]
I'M DEADLY SERIOUS.

14:06.967 --> 14:10.600
THESE KIDS WANT TO LEARN.
BACK OF THE LINE.

14:10.600 --> 14:13.233
[ SCOFFS ]

14:13.233 --> 14:14.274
THANK YOU.

14:14.274 --> 14:17.107
NOW, YOU NOTICE
THAT THE ABSORBED TWIN

14:17.107 --> 14:19.689
GETS IT BLOOD SUPPLY
FROM THE RENAL ARTERY.

14:19.689 --> 14:22.532
FIRST GLANCE --
NOTHING SPECIAL.

14:22.532 --> 14:25.535
TAKE A SECOND LOOK, AND...
THE MONA LISA.

14:25.535 --> 14:27.867
WE WILL START BY CUTTING
THROUGH THE ADHESIONS.

14:27.867 --> 14:30.580
ONCE THAT OCCURS, WE'LL MOVE ON
TO THE RIGHT --
WE'RE NOT TAKING HIM OUT.

14:30.580 --> 14:32.332
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

14:32.332 --> 14:34.544
YOU HEARD THE MAN.

14:34.544 --> 14:36.917
MY LITTLE TWIN
IS AN INCREDIBLY RARE FIND.

14:36.917 --> 14:38.498
UH, YES.

14:38.498 --> 14:43.003
Y-Y-YES, IT IS, GREG, BUT, UH,
IT...STILL HAS TO COME OUT.

14:43.003 --> 14:45.175
YOU WANT TO DESTROY
THE MONA LISA?

14:45.175 --> 14:47.177
NO.

14:47.177 --> 14:48.638
I WON'T SIGN THE CONSENT.

14:51.641 --> 14:53.063
[ CASH REGISTER BEEPS ]

14:53.063 --> 14:54.274
[ SLURPING ]

14:54.274 --> 14:55.435
I MEAN, YOU'RE FIXING
BABY HEARTS,

14:55.435 --> 14:57.397
DEREK'S MAPPING THE BRAIN,
AND I'M --

14:57.397 --> 14:59.779
HAVE THE MOST
AMAZING SURGERY EVER.

14:59.779 --> 15:01.481
I MEAN, PLEASE,
TELL ME THIS IS PRESSING --

15:01.481 --> 15:02.442
NOWHERE NEAR THE HEART.

15:02.442 --> 15:04.654
HEY.
DID YOU SEE THIS?

15:04.654 --> 15:07.077
OH,
THAT THE ABSORBED TWIN?

15:07.077 --> 15:08.658
TECHNICALLY,
THAT'S A PEDS CASE.

15:08.658 --> 15:10.490
BACK OFF.
IT'S THE REASON I LIVE.

15:10.490 --> 15:14.294
AW, SHE'S MOPEY 'CAUSE SHE LET
A LAB RAT LOOSE IN HER LAB.

15:14.294 --> 15:15.665
BOO-HOO.
YOU GONNA EAT THAT BACON?

15:15.665 --> 15:17.497
NO, IT'S LIKE LEAVING
YOUR KIDS WITH A BABYSITTER.

15:17.497 --> 15:19.299
I MEAN, YOU SAY, "PUT THE KIDS
TO BED AT 7:00," BUT WILL THEY?

15:19.299 --> 15:22.092
OR WILL THEY DRINK
ALL YOUR TEQUILA, PASS OUT,

15:22.092 --> 15:23.673
LEAVE THE GAS ON,
THE WHOLE HOUSE BLOWS UP,

15:23.673 --> 15:24.674
AND EVERYBODY DIES?

15:24.674 --> 15:27.177
OKAY.
WHAT DO YOU THINK OF HER?

15:27.177 --> 15:28.598
SHE'S HOT, RIGHT?
HAVE YOU GIVEN UP ON MEN?

15:28.598 --> 15:30.600
NO, FOR OWEN.

15:30.600 --> 15:33.223
THERE IS THIS
INTERNET-DATING SITE.

15:33.223 --> 15:35.475
THERE ARE PAGES
OF WOMEN LIKE THIS.

15:35.475 --> 15:37.607
OWEN SHOULD BE DOING THIS,
RIGHT?
YES.

15:37.607 --> 15:38.858
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
KEEP BANGING HIM?

15:38.858 --> 15:40.820
AT LEAST
IT'S LEGAL FOR YOU GUYS.

15:40.820 --> 15:42.442
YOU KNOW, JO'S NOT GONNA SIGN
THAT STUPID LOVE CONTRACT

15:42.442 --> 15:44.364
YOU GAVE ME.
WHY NOT?

15:44.364 --> 15:45.945
OH, I DON'T KNOW.
BECAUSE IT'S STUPID.

15:45.945 --> 15:47.447
I KNEW I SHOULDN'T HAVE
GIVEN IT TO HER.

15:47.447 --> 15:49.369
JUST TELL HER IT'S
JUST A STUPID PIECE OF PAPER.

15:49.369 --> 15:51.451
YEAH, IF SHE RUNS,
I'M BLAMING YOU.

15:51.451 --> 15:53.283
SHE LOOKS LIKE SHE'S 20.
SHE'S CUTE.

15:53.283 --> 15:55.335
I HATE YOUR HUSBAND.

15:55.335 --> 15:57.287
OWEN SAID
NOT TO TALK ABOUT IT.

15:57.287 --> 15:58.498
I'M NOT.
I'M TALKING TO MYSELF.

15:58.498 --> 15:59.879
I HATE DEREK SHEPHERD.
REALLY? WHY?

15:59.879 --> 16:02.382
OH, 'CAUSE HE'S AN ARROGANT,
STEALING BASTARD.

16:02.382 --> 16:03.883
[ GASPS ]
I TOTALLY AGREE.

16:03.883 --> 16:05.545
DO YOU LADIES
THINK SHE'S HOT?

16:05.545 --> 16:07.467
[ SLURPING ]
YEAH, VERY.

16:07.467 --> 16:09.009
AND NOW I HATE YOU.

16:11.261 --> 16:13.473
NICE. OH.
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

16:13.473 --> 16:15.265
OH, NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

16:15.265 --> 16:16.306
I GOT TO GO.

16:16.306 --> 16:18.898
WHAT DID YOU?

16:18.898 --> 16:21.151
D-- HE TALKED THE MAN
OUT OF SURGERY.

16:21.151 --> 16:22.862
NOW HE LOVES
HIS LITTLE BROTHER --

16:22.862 --> 16:24.564
CAN'T BEAR
TO PART WITH HIM.

16:24.564 --> 16:27.947
WHAT?
I WAS EXPLAINING THE UNIQUENESS
OF HIS CONDITION.

16:27.947 --> 16:31.281
APPARENTLY,
MY WORDS...CAST A SPELL.

16:31.281 --> 16:33.613
AH!
Meredith: OKAY, SO,
NOW WHAT DO WE TELL HIM?

16:33.613 --> 16:36.416
HOW DO WE GET HIM BACK?
TELL HIM IT COULD HAVE ADVERSE
EFFECTS ON HIS BLOOD PRESSURE.

16:36.416 --> 16:38.708
TELL HIM IT COULD EXPLODE.
TELL HIM IT'S A DEMON.

16:38.708 --> 16:40.120
OH, THAT'S GOOD.
OKAY, STOP!

16:40.120 --> 16:42.542
I RUINED IT. I-I'LL FIX IT.
I'LL TALK TO HIM.

16:42.542 --> 16:44.714
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA SAY?
I DON'T KNOW!

16:44.714 --> 16:47.337
I'M COMING WITH YOU.

16:47.337 --> 16:49.469
THIS IS THE WORST
BIRTHDAY EVER.

16:49.469 --> 16:52.392
[ GRUNTING ] OH, HEY.
HEY, DID YOU TALK TO DR. YANG?

16:52.392 --> 16:54.224
OW! SWEET, GEEZ.

16:54.224 --> 16:55.435
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

16:55.435 --> 16:56.596
SHE...
[ GRUNTS ]

16:56.596 --> 16:58.598
SHE DIDN'T SAY.

16:58.598 --> 16:59.809
SHE WAS BUSY.

16:59.809 --> 17:01.441
OH, DAMN.

17:01.441 --> 17:04.354
SHE SAID NO.
SHE SAID NO.

17:04.354 --> 17:07.197
OHH. LOOK.

17:07.197 --> 17:08.988
THEY SAID
I'D BE DEAD BY 15.

17:08.988 --> 17:10.990
I-I DROPPED OUT
OF HIGH SCHOOL.

17:10.990 --> 17:13.573
I HITCHHIKED.
I HAD SEX.

17:13.573 --> 17:15.535
I'M HAVING THIS BABY BECAUSE
I THOUGHT I WAS GONNA DIE.

17:15.535 --> 17:18.788
NOW THAT IT'S COMING,
I REALLY WANT TO LIVE.

17:18.788 --> 17:20.960
I WANT THE CHANCE
TO BE HER MOM.

17:20.960 --> 17:23.423
SO, CAN YOU
PLEASE BRING DR. YANG IN HERE

17:23.423 --> 17:25.044
SO I CAN TALK TO HER,
PLEASE?

17:25.044 --> 17:26.926
FOR MY BABY. OH!

17:26.926 --> 17:28.338
OKAY, OKAY, BREATHE.

17:28.338 --> 17:30.510
[ Grunting ]
I AM BREATHING! [ GROANS ]

17:30.510 --> 17:33.723
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

17:33.723 --> 17:35.555
[ SIGHS ]
Alex: HEY.
WHAT ARE YOU DO--

17:35.555 --> 17:37.137
Shh.

17:37.137 --> 17:39.559
What are you doing?

17:39.559 --> 17:41.561
Webber's post-ops.
[ Sighs ]

17:41.561 --> 17:43.733
Since he got the fetus in fetu,
I get this.

17:43.733 --> 17:47.567
WELL, I'M HEADING
INTO THE FUNDOPLICATION,

17:47.567 --> 17:50.950
AND YOU'D BE THERE, TOO,
IF YOU WERE IN PEDS.

17:50.950 --> 17:52.362
NO.

17:52.362 --> 17:54.244
OKAY, LOOK, I THOUGHT IT WAS
NUTS WHEN MER GAVE IT TO ME,

17:54.244 --> 17:56.246
AND I KNEW
YOU'D HATE IT, TOO.

17:56.246 --> 17:58.658
BUT, HONEST TO GOD, IT'S JUST
A PIECE OF PAPER THAT SAYS --

17:58.658 --> 18:01.291
IT'S A LEGAL DOCUMENT, ALEX,
SO IT'S NOT JUST --

18:01.291 --> 18:03.293
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM?

18:03.293 --> 18:05.084
IN MY EXPERIENCE,
YOU SIGN PAPERS,

18:05.084 --> 18:06.546
AND IT'S A KISS OF DEATH.

18:06.546 --> 18:09.549
YOU SIGN A MARRIAGE LICENSE,
AND THE ROMANCE GOES AWAY.

18:09.549 --> 18:11.131
SHE SIGNED A DNR
TWO DAYS AGO.

18:11.131 --> 18:14.344
GUESS WHAT.
SHE'S USING IT.

18:14.344 --> 18:17.557
HEY, ALEX.
OUR GUY'S BEING PREPPED. OOH.

18:17.557 --> 18:20.059
For what?
Our fundoplication.

18:20.059 --> 18:22.642
IS THAT THE COOL TRANSORAL
THING -- CUTTING-EDGE,

18:22.642 --> 18:26.105
ONLY BEING DONE IN A FEW
TOP-LEVEL PEDS-SURG PROGRAMS?

18:26.105 --> 18:27.857
YEAH, THAT'S THE ONE.

18:27.857 --> 18:30.820
OKAY. LET'S DO IT.

18:30.820 --> 18:33.363
[ SIGHS ]

18:34.324 --> 18:36.115
I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU.

18:36.115 --> 18:38.498
Derek: OKAY,
THEN JUST LISTEN.

18:38.498 --> 18:40.660
IF YOU UNDERSTOOD WHAT THE
BRAIN-MAPPING PROJECT CAN DO,

18:40.660 --> 18:42.081
YOU WOULD SHARE
YOUR TECHNOLOGY.

18:42.081 --> 18:43.453
OH, SHARE?

18:43.453 --> 18:46.376
I'M SHARING NOW?
YOU'RE STEALING IT.

18:46.376 --> 18:47.547
YOU'RE STEALING IT.

18:47.547 --> 18:49.379
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
[ SIGHS ]

18:49.379 --> 18:50.750
CALLIE, THE BRAIN

18:50.750 --> 18:55.555
HAS MORE NERVE CELLS
THAN HUMANS ON EARTH.

18:55.555 --> 18:58.518
WE WANT TO UNDERSTAND HOW
ALL THOSE NEURONS INTERACT,

18:58.518 --> 19:00.220
SO WE'RE GONNA START
WITH A SMALLER GROUP

19:00.220 --> 19:02.392
LIKE EVERYBODY HERE
IN THE HOSPITAL.

19:02.392 --> 19:03.813
AND WE'RE
GONNA DETERMINE HOW

19:03.813 --> 19:06.566
THEY INTERACT
WITH EACH OTHER AND TALK.

19:06.566 --> 19:07.567
PLEASE, STOP.
AND THEN WE MOVE OUT.

19:07.567 --> 19:08.608
STOP PATRONIZING ME,
ALL RIGHT?

19:08.608 --> 19:09.569
YOU'RE JUST SAYING
THAT YOUR THING

19:09.569 --> 19:10.650
IS MORE IMPORTANT
THAN MINE.

19:10.650 --> 19:11.941
I'M SAYING MY THING
FEEDS YOUR THING.

19:11.941 --> 19:13.983
IT WILL REVOLUTIONIZE
OUR UNDERSTANDING

19:13.983 --> 19:15.485
OF WHAT IT MEANS
TO BE HUMAN.

19:15.485 --> 19:16.906
AND YET, YOU WOULD HAVE
NEVER HAD THE SENSORS

19:16.906 --> 19:18.868
IF IT WEREN'T FOR MY THING,
YOU SELFISH --

19:18.868 --> 19:20.450
SELFISH?

19:20.450 --> 19:23.333
HERE!
LET ME SHOW YOU A DIAGRAM.

19:23.333 --> 19:25.995
THIS IS YOU.

19:25.995 --> 19:27.377
I'M AN ASTERISK?
NO.

19:27.377 --> 19:30.550
YOU THINK YOU ARE THE WHITE-HOT
CENTER OF THE UNIVERSE.

19:30.550 --> 19:34.133
ALSO, IT LOOKS LIKE
A BUTTHOLE.

19:34.133 --> 19:36.966
EITHER WAY, IT WORKS.

19:41.641 --> 19:43.933
SHERYLL, THIS IS DR. YANG.
[ COUGHS ]

19:43.933 --> 19:44.894
OH, HI.

19:44.894 --> 19:47.227
DR. YANG, I-I'D HUG YOU,
BUT -- OW!

19:47.227 --> 19:48.438
JUST BREATHE.
I CAN WAIT.

19:48.438 --> 19:49.809
NO, I'M FINE.

19:49.809 --> 19:52.071
UH, MY DOCTOR WANTED TO PUT ME
ON A TRANSPLANT LIST,

19:52.071 --> 19:54.113
BUT I HEARD ABOUT YOUR SUCCESS
WITH BABY NATHAN.

19:54.113 --> 19:56.115
[ GROANS ]
OH.

19:56.115 --> 19:59.579
DR. ROSS, THIS IS THE PATIENT
YOU ALREADY SPOKE TO ME ABOUT.

19:59.579 --> 20:00.740
LISTEN -- I KNOW YOU'RE ONLY
LOOKING FOR LITTLE KIDS,

20:00.740 --> 20:01.911
BUT CAN YOU PLEASE,
JUST --

20:01.911 --> 20:03.122
[ Grunting ]
PLEASE! AAH!

20:03.122 --> 20:06.536
YOU KNOW, JUST LET ME...
TAKE A LISTEN HERE.

20:06.536 --> 20:09.379
OH, MY GOODNESS.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.
OKAY.

20:11.751 --> 20:16.966
YOU HAVE A SLIGHT MURMUR,
BUT, BESIDES THAT, YOU ARE WELL.

20:16.966 --> 20:19.299
YOUR O.B. WILL MONITOR
YOUR CARDIAC FUNCTION,

20:19.299 --> 20:21.971
AND PAGE ME IF THERE ARE
ANY COMPLICATIONS.

20:21.971 --> 20:23.553
GOOD LUCK.

20:23.553 --> 20:25.975
DR. ROSS, A MINUTE?

20:27.106 --> 20:29.479
I'M SORRY.

20:29.479 --> 20:30.900
SHE JUST REALLY WANTED TO HAVE
A CHANCE TO PLEAD HER CASE.

20:30.900 --> 20:33.152
THAT WAS OUT OF LINE.
I ALREADY SAID NO.

20:33.152 --> 20:34.564
I KNOW IT WAS WRONG.
I'M SORRY.

20:34.564 --> 20:37.066
SHE DOESN'T MEET THE CRITERIA.
IT'S THAT SIMPLE.

20:37.066 --> 20:38.408
[ SIGHS ]

20:38.408 --> 20:41.661
I KNOW IT'S HARD BECAUSE
THEY'RE KIDS AND THEY'RE DYING.

20:41.661 --> 20:44.163
AND THEY'VE GOT THEIR STORIES
AND LIVES AND FAMILY --

20:44.163 --> 20:45.495
WELL, SHE DOESN'T!

20:45.495 --> 20:48.037
HER PARENTS
DON'T TALK TO HER.
ROSS, STOP IT.

20:48.037 --> 20:50.460
YOU'RE TOO EMOTIONALLY INVOLVED,
AND YOU'VE GOTTEN HER HOPES UP.

20:50.460 --> 20:52.832
IT'S GONNA BE WORSE ON HER
WHEN YOU TELL HER NO.

20:52.832 --> 20:54.133
[ SHERYLL GROANS ]

20:54.133 --> 20:56.336
[ SIGHS ]

20:56.336 --> 20:58.928
DO YOUR JOB.

20:58.928 --> 21:01.140
DO YOU HAVE
MY DISCHARGE PAPERS?

21:01.140 --> 21:03.843
UH [SIGHS]
NO. NO, NO, I DON'T.

21:03.843 --> 21:05.385
I THINK
YOU NEED TO RECONSIDER.

21:05.385 --> 21:06.846
YOU NEED TO HAVE
THIS THING REMOVED, GREG.

21:06.846 --> 21:08.848
DR. WEBER, YOU SAID
IT WAS INCREDIBLY RARE.

21:08.848 --> 21:11.230
AND IT'S MINE.

21:11.230 --> 21:12.602
PEOPLE CHUCK STUFF
ALL THE TIME,

21:12.602 --> 21:13.983
NO CLUE OF THE --
THE VALUE OF THE THING

21:13.983 --> 21:15.605
THAT THEY'RE
THROWING AWAY.

21:15.605 --> 21:17.447
FINDING TREASURE IN THEIR TRASH
IS WHAT I DO.

21:17.447 --> 21:18.818
AND I DIDN'T
HAVE TO DIG THROUGH

21:18.818 --> 21:21.821
ANYONE'S YARD-SALE CRAP
TO FIND THIS.

21:21.821 --> 21:23.743
IT WAS INSIDE OF ME
ALL ALONG.

21:23.743 --> 21:25.955
Jodi: THIS IS A WAD
OF BONES AND TEETH.

21:25.955 --> 21:29.168
IT'S NOT SOME CRUMMY BOX
OF VHS TAPES.

21:29.168 --> 21:30.370
WE'VE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

21:30.370 --> 21:32.752
ANALOG'S COMING BACK
IN A BIG WAY.

21:32.752 --> 21:34.834
Meredith: JUST BECAUSE IT'S RARE
DOESN'T MEAN IT HAS VALUE.

21:34.834 --> 21:37.216
A HEART HAS VALUE.
A LIVER HAS VALUE.

21:37.216 --> 21:39.799
ACTUALLY,
I'M ON GREG'S SIDE HERE.

21:39.799 --> 21:40.920
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

21:40.920 --> 21:43.343
PEOPLE DO THROW THINGS AWAY
TOO EASILY.

21:43.343 --> 21:45.765
THEY THROW OUT PEOPLE
JUST LIKE THAT.

21:45.765 --> 21:46.926
THEY'RE DONE WITH YOU,

21:46.926 --> 21:48.808
AND THEN THEY THROW YOU OUT
WITH THE TRASH.

21:48.808 --> 21:49.769
SIR.
I'M NOT GONNA
DO THAT, GREG.

21:49.769 --> 21:52.311
STOP!
YEAH, STOP.

21:52.311 --> 21:54.063
OKAY, GREG,
I HAVE A PROPOSITION FOR YOU.

21:54.063 --> 21:55.775
YOU LET ME REMOVE
THIS FETUS IN FETU,

21:55.775 --> 21:59.439
AND I PROMISE YOU
I WON'T THROW IT IN THE TRASH.

21:59.439 --> 22:01.651
I'LL THROW IT IN A JAR,
AND YOU CAN TAKE IT HOME.

22:01.651 --> 22:02.992
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU AREN'T SERIOUS.

22:02.992 --> 22:05.365
IT'LL LOOK A HELL OF
A LOT BETTER ON A SHELF
THAN IN YOUR BELLY.

22:05.365 --> 22:06.786
AND YOU WON'T HAVE
THAT PAIN ANYMORE.

22:06.786 --> 22:08.998
YOU CAN DO THAT?

22:08.998 --> 22:10.870
I DO IT ALL THE TIME.

22:10.870 --> 22:12.662
IT COMES DOWN TO THIS.

22:12.662 --> 22:14.834
MY RESEARCH IS
JUST AS IMPORTANT AS YOURS.

22:14.834 --> 22:16.045
YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT MICROSCOPIC NEURONS.

22:16.045 --> 22:17.457
I'M TALKING ABOUT
GIVING A PERSON

22:17.457 --> 22:18.668
THE ABILITY
TO WALK AGAIN.

22:18.668 --> 22:19.799
IT'S JUST AS IMPORTANT!

22:19.799 --> 22:21.170
AND YOU WOULDN'T HAVE
COME UP WITH THE SENSORS

22:21.170 --> 22:22.592
IF IT WASN'T FOR MY WORK.

22:22.592 --> 22:25.805
THE SENSORS WERE AN ANSWER
TO A QUESTION THAT I ASKED YOU.

22:25.805 --> 22:27.266
IT WAS MY ANSWER!
WH--

22:27.266 --> 22:28.678
DON'T FIGHT THIS, CALLIE.
YOU DON'T WANT TO.

22:28.678 --> 22:31.931
OH, WHY, 'CAUSE YOU HAVE
GOVERNMENT LAWYERS NOW?

22:31.931 --> 22:33.393
I'M NOT GONNA BE BULLIED.
YOU DON'T HAVE A CASE!

22:33.393 --> 22:35.775
MY NAME IS ON THE MATERIAL,
AND MY NAME IS ON THE PATENTS.

22:35.775 --> 22:37.777
THEY'RE MINE.
YOU CAN HEAR IT FROM ME NOW.

22:37.777 --> 22:40.279
OR YOU CAN HEAR IT
FROM A JUDGE IN COURT.

22:40.279 --> 22:42.862
MY SUGGESTION IS
TO SAVE YOUR TIME AND MONEY.

22:42.862 --> 22:45.945
[ SIGHS ]
LISTEN TO ME...
AS YOUR FRIEND.

22:47.907 --> 22:49.869
I'M SORRY.

22:49.869 --> 22:51.951
I FEEL TERRIBLE.

22:51.951 --> 22:55.755
THERE'S A REASON
YOU FEEL TERRIBLE.

22:55.755 --> 22:58.167
IT'S 'CAUSE IT'S THE WRONG THING
TO DO, AND YOU KNOW IT.

22:58.167 --> 22:59.669
YOU'RE NOT USED
TO ANSWERING TO PEOPLE,

22:59.669 --> 23:00.880
AND NOW YOU HAVE
THE PRESIDENT HIMSELF

23:00.880 --> 23:01.881
CALLING YOU ON THE PHONE.

23:01.881 --> 23:04.504
AND YOU'RE AFRAID
TO SAY NO...

23:04.504 --> 23:08.097
EVEN THOUGH YOU KNOW
THIS IS 100% WRONG.

23:10.349 --> 23:11.931
YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON.

23:11.931 --> 23:15.975
♪ OH, IT'S YOU ♪
THAT'S WHY YOU FEEL BAD --
'CAUSE YOU SHOULD.

23:15.975 --> 23:17.727
♪ I KNOW ♪

23:17.727 --> 23:19.779
Owen: DOWN TO SEVEN --
THAT'S FAST.

23:19.779 --> 23:21.360
I KNOW WHAT I WANT.

23:21.360 --> 23:22.942
UH, DID YOU
DO THE PROFILE?

23:22.942 --> 23:25.735
WHAT? THE DATING THING?
NO, NO.

23:25.735 --> 23:27.737
CRISTINA, I-I'VE SPENT MY
MORNING TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

23:27.737 --> 23:31.030
A WAY TO FIX THIS THING
BETWEEN TORRES AND SHEPHERD.

23:31.030 --> 23:33.242
I HAVEN'T HAD TIME.
SIT. I'LL DO IT FOR YOU.

23:33.242 --> 23:35.244
DESCRIBE YOURSELF.

23:35.244 --> 23:36.836
NO.
STUBBORN.

23:36.836 --> 23:38.297
LISTEN --
I'M NOT BEING STUBBORN.

23:38.297 --> 23:39.709
I'M JUST --
SMART, ATHLETIC.

23:39.709 --> 23:40.960
LISTEN --
I'M TOO BUSY TO --

23:40.960 --> 23:43.963
"A BUSY PROFESSIONAL
SEEKS" -- WHAT?

23:43.963 --> 23:45.545
NOTHING.
I SEEK NOTHING.

23:45.545 --> 23:49.008
AH, "SEEKS SAME, SOMEONE WHO IS
PASSIONATE ABOUT HER WORK..."

23:49.008 --> 23:52.852
[ SCOFFS ]
"...SOMEONE WHO'S..."
COME ON. WHAT?

23:52.852 --> 23:54.053
FINE. FINE.

23:54.053 --> 23:58.267
UM...SOMEONE WHO
DOESN'T CARE TO COOK

23:58.267 --> 24:01.360
OR GET OUT OF BED
WHEN IT'S NOT A WORK DAY.

24:01.360 --> 24:05.945
SOMEONE WHO SLEEPS
SO SOUNDLY AND PEACEFULLY

24:05.945 --> 24:09.408
THAT...I HAVE TO CHECK
HER PULSE SOMETIMES.

24:09.408 --> 24:11.991
[ SIGHS ]

24:11.991 --> 24:15.835
SOMEONE
WHO'S SUFFERED...

24:15.835 --> 24:17.997
AND UNDERSTANDS
SUFFERING.

24:17.997 --> 24:19.629
I'D KEEP IT MORE UPBEAT.

24:19.629 --> 24:23.212
D-- TO THE POINT
THAT I DON'T HAVE TO SAY A WORD.

24:23.212 --> 24:26.846
SHE JUST --
SHE JUST LOOKS AT ME AND SEES

24:26.846 --> 24:31.641
WHO I AM AND HOW I FEEL...
AND ACCEPTS IT.

24:31.641 --> 24:33.432
YOU KNOW,
SHE DOESN'T TRY TO CHANGE IT,

24:33.432 --> 24:34.644
DOESN'T WANT TO CHANGE IT.

24:34.644 --> 24:37.436
♪ FALLING IN LOVE
IS SO BITTERSWEET ♪

24:37.436 --> 24:39.649
THAT PERSON.

24:39.649 --> 24:43.192
♪ THIS LOVE IS STRONG,
WHY DO I FEEL WEAK? ♪

24:43.192 --> 24:45.985
THERE'S A BILLION PEOPLE
OUT THERE. [ INHALES DEEPLY ]

24:45.985 --> 24:49.569
BUT I IMAGINE...
THERE'S ONLY ONE HER.

24:55.785 --> 24:58.618
♪ OH, WAKE ME ♪

24:58.618 --> 25:00.419
♪ I'M SHAKING ♪

25:00.419 --> 25:02.421
♪ WISH I HAD YOU NEAR ME NOW ♪

25:02.421 --> 25:04.834
I AM HAPPY
TO SIGN THE DOCUMENT.

25:04.834 --> 25:06.626
THAT'S WONDERFUL.

25:06.626 --> 25:11.801
♪ SAID THERE'S NO MISTAKING ♪

25:11.801 --> 25:15.805
♪ WHAT I FEEL IS REALLY LOVE ♪

25:15.805 --> 25:17.436
I DON'T HAVE A PEN.

25:17.436 --> 25:19.228
NO, SWEETHEART,
YOU DON'T...

25:19.228 --> 25:20.850
ACTUALLY SIGN IT HERE.

25:20.850 --> 25:22.441
♪ HOW WILL I KNOW? ♪
YOU REVIEW IT WITH YOUR LAWYER,

25:22.441 --> 25:25.605
AND HE WILL THEN CONFER
WITH OUR FAMILY LAWYER.

25:25.605 --> 25:27.607
♪ HOW WILL I KNOW? ♪
I-I WILL CONSULT
A LAWYER.

25:27.607 --> 25:29.609
GOOD.

25:29.609 --> 25:31.701
NOW, LET'S TALK
ABOUT THE CHILDREN.

25:31.701 --> 25:32.862
♪ HOW WILL I KNOW? ♪
[ Sighing ] OH, MY GOD.

25:32.862 --> 25:34.493
WILL YOU HAVE CHILDREN?

25:34.493 --> 25:36.866
YES.
YES.

25:36.866 --> 25:38.207
♪ HOW WILL I KNOW? ♪
YES. I SAID, "YES."

25:38.207 --> 25:40.960
IN WHAT RELIGIOUS TRADITION
WILL THEY BE RAISED?

25:40.960 --> 25:42.331
♪ HOW WILL I KNOW? ♪
WE DON'T KNOW.

25:42.331 --> 25:44.543
WE HAVEN'T TALKED ABOUT
WHAT RELIGIOUS TRADITION

25:44.543 --> 25:47.627
WE WILL OR WON'T RAISE
OUR THEORETICAL CHILDREN IN YET.

25:47.627 --> 25:49.759
THAT'S A CONVERSATION
YOU MIGHT WANT TO HAVE.

25:49.759 --> 25:53.222
AVERY CHILDREN BECOME
AVERY FOUNDATION BOARD MEMBERS.

25:53.222 --> 25:57.807
THE FOUNDATION CONTROLS
$480 MILLION IN CHARITABLE FUNDS

25:57.807 --> 25:59.849
FOR THE ADVANCEMENT
OF MEDICINE.

25:59.849 --> 26:01.230
[ SIGHS ] YEAH.
WHAT?

26:01.230 --> 26:04.023
YOUR CHILDREN,
WHEN THEY ARE 15,

26:04.023 --> 26:06.816
WILL START SITTING IN
ON BOARD MEETINGS, YOU KNOW,

26:06.816 --> 26:08.988
BEGIN TO LEARN THE BUSINESS,
LIKE JACKSON DID.

26:08.988 --> 26:13.572
WHEN THEY ARE 18, THEY WILL
GAIN A SEAT ON THE BOARD.

26:13.572 --> 26:16.575
THEY WILL BE
VOTING MEMBERS.

26:16.575 --> 26:21.160
YOU ARE A BORN-AGAIN CHRISTIAN,
WHO I PRESUME IS PRO-LIFE.

26:21.160 --> 26:22.331
THAT'S RIGHT.

26:22.331 --> 26:24.123
WILL YOUR CHILDREN
BE TAUGHT THAT PEOPLE

26:24.123 --> 26:25.965
WHO ARE PRO-CHOICE
GO TO HELL

26:25.965 --> 26:27.086
OR THEIR PRO-CHOICE
FATHER

26:27.086 --> 26:28.507
IS GOING TO HELL
OR THEIR GRANDMOTHER?

26:28.507 --> 26:29.588
WAIT.
WHOA!

26:29.588 --> 26:31.380
I-I DON'T THINK
ANYONE IS GOING TO HELL.

26:31.380 --> 26:33.592
I-I-IT'S SO MUCH MORE
COMPLICATED THAN THAT.

26:33.592 --> 26:36.595
WILL THEY STOP SUPPORTING
MEDICAL INSTITUTIONS

26:36.595 --> 26:39.598
THAT PERFORM ABORTIONS
OR PROVIDE INFORMATION

26:39.598 --> 26:42.181
ABOUT ABORTIONS LIKE,
FOR EXAMPLE, THIS HOSPITAL?

26:42.181 --> 26:45.564
WILL THEY VOTE TO STOP
SUPPORTING STEM-CELL RESEARCH?

26:45.564 --> 26:47.226
WE'D ALL LIKE TO THINK
THAT THE PROBLEM AT THE TABLE

26:47.226 --> 26:48.818
IS THE MEDDLING
MOTHER-IN-LAW

26:48.818 --> 26:50.940
WHO DIDN'T GET TO WALK
HER SON DOWN THE AISLE,

26:50.940 --> 26:53.943
BUT I HAVE BUILT
A MASSIVE INSTITUTION

26:53.943 --> 26:56.946
WITH MY BLOOD AND MY SWEAT,
AND YOU WILL INHERIT IT.

26:56.946 --> 26:59.739
AND, ONE DAY,
YOUR CHILDREN WILL CONTROL IT.

26:59.739 --> 27:02.161
AND I DON'T GET THE IMPRESSION
THAT EITHER OF YOU

27:02.161 --> 27:06.125
HAS GIVEN A MOMENT'S THOUGHT
TO WHAT THAT MEANS!

27:10.299 --> 27:13.302
HELLO, LITTLE BROTHER.

27:13.302 --> 27:15.134
I SEE A FINGER.

27:15.134 --> 27:17.136
NO, TWO...
THREE FINGERS.

27:17.136 --> 27:18.557
GROSS!

27:18.557 --> 27:19.809
WHERE?

27:19.809 --> 27:20.970
HE JUST WANTS TO
TRY THE PRINTER.

27:20.970 --> 27:22.181
WHY DOES HE NEED TO?

27:22.181 --> 27:23.562
BECAUSE
IT'S WHY HE'S HERE.

27:23.562 --> 27:24.974
AND AS LONG AS YOU
WON'T LET HIM DO ANYTHING,

27:24.974 --> 27:26.185
I CAN'T BE IN HERE.

27:26.185 --> 27:27.186
TELL HIM I SAID NO.

27:29.108 --> 27:32.071
IS -- IS THAT AN EAR?
Man: AN EAR?

27:32.071 --> 27:33.272
NO. THAT'S A LUNG.
Woman: THAT'S A LUNG.

27:33.272 --> 27:34.653
BUT THAT IS A TOOTH.
A TOOTH.

27:34.653 --> 27:38.447
OH, AND THAT
IS A SPINAL COLUMN.

27:38.447 --> 27:40.740
LOOK!
EVERY DAMN VERTEBRAE.

27:40.740 --> 27:43.162
[ ALL GASPING ]
I STILL WANT TO KNOW WHAT
YOU SAID TO GET HIM TO CONSENT.

27:43.162 --> 27:45.204
HE PROMISED HIM
A DOGGY BAG.

27:45.204 --> 27:47.166
YOU DIDN'T.

27:47.166 --> 27:49.208
I DID.

27:49.208 --> 27:51.420
HE'S RIGHT.
IT'S PART OF HIM.

27:51.420 --> 27:53.212
HE SHOULD BE ABLE TO HAVE IT
AND SHARE IT.

27:53.212 --> 27:56.055
THIS IS
OF GREAT MEDICAL INTEREST.

27:56.055 --> 27:58.057
THAT'S VALUABLE.

27:58.057 --> 28:00.259
YOU DON'T...
HIDE IT INSIDE

28:00.259 --> 28:05.564
OF...SOME BASEMENT
OR...LET IT ROT AWAY.

28:05.564 --> 28:06.936
YOU SHARE IT.

28:06.936 --> 28:09.899
YOU LET PEOPLE BENEFIT
FROM IT BECAUSE, IF YOU DO,

28:09.899 --> 28:13.192
YOU CAN CHANGE
THE FACE OF MEDICINE.

28:13.192 --> 28:15.024
OH, MY GOD, I'M GONNA
SAY THIS TO YOU FOR THE
LAST TIME, ALL RIGHT?

28:15.024 --> 28:17.987
THIS RELATIONSHIP IS NOT NEW.
THIS DECISION WAS NOT RASH.

28:17.987 --> 28:19.779
YOU ONLY FEEL THAT WAY

28:19.779 --> 28:21.781
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
GET TO WEIGH IN ON IT.

28:21.781 --> 28:23.452
BECAUSE YOU
DIDN'T INCLUDE ME IN IT,

28:23.452 --> 28:25.284
LIKE EVERYTHING ELSE
IN YOUR LIFE.

28:25.284 --> 28:26.245
I DON'T
NEED TO INCLUDE YOU!

28:26.245 --> 28:27.787
YOU INCLUDE YOURSELF
IN EVERYTHING ALWAYS!

28:27.787 --> 28:29.128
STOP! OH, STOP IT!
STOP IT, BOTH OF YOU!

28:29.128 --> 28:30.629
APRIL, SWEETHEART,
DON'T --

28:30.629 --> 28:32.211
[ SLAMS TABLE ]
NO, STOP IT!

28:32.211 --> 28:35.044
[ SIGHS ] YOU'RE RIGHT.

28:35.044 --> 28:36.836
THERE ARE A LOT OF THINGS
WE STILL HAVEN'T FIGURED OUT,

28:36.836 --> 28:39.218
BUT WE WILL FIGURE THEM OUT --
JACKSON AND I.

28:39.218 --> 28:42.261
BUT IF YOU -- IF YOU THINK
THAT I AM JUDGING YOU

28:42.261 --> 28:43.342
OR ANYONE BECAUSE
OF MY BELIEFS,

28:43.342 --> 28:46.766
THEN I'M -- I'M SO SORRY
BECAUSE I'M NOT.

28:46.766 --> 28:49.108
THAT IS NOT ME.
AND -- [ SIGHS ]

28:49.108 --> 28:51.650
I-I-I WOULD LOVE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THAT SOMETIME,

28:51.650 --> 28:54.443
BUT I-I-IF IT'S OUR CHILDREN
THAT YOU ARE SO CONCERNED ABOUT,

28:54.443 --> 28:56.235
IF THEY DISAGREE WITH YOU
ON SOME THINGS,

28:56.235 --> 28:57.236
IF THAT'S NOT OKAY
WITH YOU,

28:57.236 --> 28:59.278
THEN [SIGHS]
I-I-I DON'T -- I DON'T KNOW.

28:59.278 --> 29:00.409
RESTRUCTURE THE BOARD?

29:00.409 --> 29:02.701
I'M -- I'M MAKING THIS UP.
I HAVE NO IDEA HOW IT WORKS.

29:02.701 --> 29:05.915
CLEARLY.
LOOK, THE POINT IS THERE
WILL BE A WAY TO FIGURE IT OUT.

29:05.915 --> 29:08.918
WE DID SOMETHING
THAT WASN'T RESPONSIBLE,

29:08.918 --> 29:10.499
BUT WE DID IT
BECAUSE WE LOVE EACH OTHER

29:10.499 --> 29:13.292
AND WE WANT TO SPEND
EVERY DAY TOGETHER UNTIL WE DIE.

29:13.292 --> 29:14.673
I AM SORRY.

29:14.673 --> 29:17.466
NO, YOU DON'T HAVE TO
APOLOGIZE TO HER.
I DO.

29:17.466 --> 29:19.298
I DO.
WE GOT MARRIED.

29:19.298 --> 29:20.679
WE HAD A WEDDING,
AND ALL SHE GOT

29:20.679 --> 29:23.973
WAS A PHONE CALL
AFTER IT WAS OVER.

29:23.973 --> 29:25.144
IF OUR KIDS DO THAT,
I WILL --

29:25.144 --> 29:27.146
I WILL KILL THEM
WITH MY BARE HANDS.

29:27.146 --> 29:30.059
WE MADE A HUGE MESS.

29:30.059 --> 29:33.152
WE HURT MATTHEW,
AND WE HURT STEPHANIE.

29:33.152 --> 29:35.895
AND WE HURT YOU.

29:35.895 --> 29:39.068
AND I AM SO SORRY.

29:39.068 --> 29:41.280
AND I'M GONNA SPEND THE NEXT
I DON'T KNOW HOW MANY YEARS

29:41.280 --> 29:45.284
TRYING TO
MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

29:45.284 --> 29:49.288
APOLOGIZE TO YOUR MOM.
♪ BUT MAKING MISTAKES ♪

29:49.288 --> 29:52.081
[ SIGHS ]
COME ON.

29:52.081 --> 29:54.463
♪ IS A PART
OF LIFE'S IMPERFECTIONS ♪

29:54.463 --> 29:57.086
♪ BORN OF THE YEARS ♪

29:57.086 --> 29:58.087
♪ IS IT SO WRONG? ♪

29:58.087 --> 29:59.468
CAN YOU STAND UP?

29:59.468 --> 30:04.683
♪ WE'RE ONLY HUMAN AFTER ALL ♪

30:06.265 --> 30:08.637
[ SIGHS ]
♪ DRAWN IN THE STREAM ♪

30:08.637 --> 30:10.639
WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU THINKING?
♪ OF UNDEFINED ILLUSION ♪

30:10.639 --> 30:12.431
I LOVE HER.
[ SCOFFS ]

30:12.431 --> 30:14.523
[ Chuckling ] MOM.

30:14.523 --> 30:17.146
AND I AM SORRY.

30:17.146 --> 30:20.529
♪ THOSE DIAMOND DREAMS ♪
BUT I LOVE HER.

30:20.529 --> 30:23.032
♪ THEY CAN'T
DISGUISE THE TRUTH ♪
SHE'S THE ONE.

30:23.032 --> 30:26.615
YOU COULD HAVE HAD
GRANDMA'S CAKE TOPPER.

30:26.615 --> 30:29.248
♪ THAT THERE'S SOMETHING
ABOUT YOU ♪
[ Voice breaking ]
IT'S LIMOGES.

30:29.248 --> 30:31.750
I KNOW. I KNOW.

30:31.750 --> 30:32.751
♪ BABY, SO RIGHT ♪
[ CRYING ]

30:32.751 --> 30:34.043
I'M SURE IT'S LOVELY.

30:34.043 --> 30:35.414
OW.

30:35.414 --> 30:36.835
OKAY.

30:36.835 --> 30:40.049
♪ I WOULDN'T BE WITHOUT YOU ♪
[ SIGHS, SNIFFLES ]

30:40.049 --> 30:41.881
♪ BABY, TONIGHT ♪

30:41.881 --> 30:43.012
Sheryll: [ Sobbing ]
CAN'T DO IT! IT HURTS.

30:43.012 --> 30:44.223
Jill: THE EPIDURAL'S
WORN OFF, SHERYLL.

30:44.223 --> 30:45.594
YOU'VE REALLY
GOT TO START PUSHING.

30:45.594 --> 30:48.017
I CAN'T. I'M TRYING.
I SWEAR I CAN'T DO IT.

30:48.017 --> 30:50.389
GOD,
I JUST WANT MY MAMA!

30:50.389 --> 30:52.972
SOMEBODY, PLEASE,
CALL MY MOM! AAH!

30:52.972 --> 30:54.233
SHERYLL,
YOUR BABY'S ALMOST HERE.

30:54.233 --> 30:56.185
JUST HANG IN THERE.
I CAN'T!

30:56.185 --> 30:58.027
I CAN'T.
CAN YOU PLEASE CALL HER?

30:58.027 --> 31:01.190
TELL HER I'M REALLY SORRY, AND
I NEED HER REALLY, REALLY BADLY.

31:01.190 --> 31:03.572
I CAN'T DO IT.
I JUST NEED MY MAMA.

31:03.572 --> 31:05.364
[ GROANS ]
HER BLOOD PRESSURE'S
SKYROCKETING.

31:05.364 --> 31:06.365
[ RAPID BEEPING ]
PREP AN O.R. FOR A C-SECTION.

31:06.365 --> 31:07.536
WE'LL CALL YOUR MOM,
OKAY?

31:07.536 --> 31:09.118
BUT YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO DO THIS ON YOUR OWN.

31:09.118 --> 31:11.160
I KNOW YOU CAN.
JUST PUSH.

31:11.160 --> 31:13.953
[ SCREAMS ]

31:13.953 --> 31:16.165
COME ON, SHERYLL. PUSH.

31:16.165 --> 31:17.957
[ SCREAMS ]

31:17.957 --> 31:19.298
ONE MORE TIME. PUSH!

31:19.298 --> 31:22.501
[ SCREAMS ]

31:22.501 --> 31:25.094
♪ IT'S NOT SO WRONG ♪
[ PANTING ]

31:25.094 --> 31:26.305
[ BABY CRYING ]

31:26.305 --> 31:30.509
♪ WE'RE ONLY HUMAN AFTER ALL ♪

31:30.509 --> 31:33.102
SHERYLL, YOU DID IT.
I DID IT?

31:33.102 --> 31:35.774
YOU DID IT, SHERYLL.
I --

31:35.774 --> 31:37.316
[ SOBBING ]

31:37.316 --> 31:39.398
♪ OOH, OOH ♪

31:39.398 --> 31:41.150
[ Ringing ]

31:41.150 --> 31:43.902
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

31:43.902 --> 31:46.485
Derek: HEY, LLOYD.

31:46.485 --> 31:49.488
HOW'S EVERYTHING
AT THE N.I.H.?

31:49.488 --> 31:51.290
UH, HELLO, DEREK.

31:51.290 --> 31:53.292
I -- WE, UH,
STILL CAN'T SEE YOU.

31:53.292 --> 31:54.703
YEAH,
WE'RE WORKING ON THAT.

31:54.703 --> 31:57.166
LLOYD, I HAVE
DR. CALLIE TORRES HERE.

31:57.166 --> 31:58.998
SHE AND I DEVELOPED
THE SENSORS TOGETHER.

31:58.998 --> 32:00.589
HI, LLOYD.
HE CAN'T SEE YOU.

32:00.589 --> 32:03.212
OH.

32:03.212 --> 32:04.964
LOOK, LLOYD, I'M AFRAID
THIS WHOLE PROPRIETARY THING

32:04.964 --> 32:06.095
ISN'T GOING TO WORK.

32:06.095 --> 32:09.308
DR. TORRES' AND MY WORK HAS
TO CONTINUE WITH OUR SENSORS.

32:09.308 --> 32:11.720
DEREK, UH, BEFORE WE, UH --
WE CONTINUE,

32:11.720 --> 32:14.143
I SHOULD TELL YOU
THAT WE ARE HERE

32:14.143 --> 32:17.816
WITH SOME FOLKS FROM THE N.I.H.
AND, UH, THE WHITE HOUSE.

32:17.816 --> 32:18.978
HERE WE ARE.

32:18.978 --> 32:21.440
GARY NEAL,
DIRECTOR OF N.I.B.S.,

32:21.440 --> 32:26.275
AND SID GARRET,
OUR PRESIDENTIAL LIAISON

32:26.275 --> 32:28.117
FOR THE BIOETHICS COMMITTEE,
AND THIS IS

32:28.117 --> 32:32.121
ROBIN MARKS OF THE
EUROPEAN BRAIN INITIATIVE,

32:32.121 --> 32:34.243
AND YOU KNOW, OF COURSE,
LINDA McCRARY.

32:34.243 --> 32:37.286
AND, UH, I -- I'M SORRY.
I FORGOT YOUR NAME.

32:37.286 --> 32:38.667
YEAH, I'M GLAD
YOU'RE ALL THERE.

32:38.667 --> 32:40.289
ACTUALLY, UM,
THIS AFFECTS ALL OF YOU.

32:40.289 --> 32:43.792
LLOYD, OUR WORK TO MAP THE BRAIN
IS LIKE THE BRAIN ITSELF.

32:43.792 --> 32:45.344
IT'S DEPENDENT
UPON CONNECTIONS,

32:45.344 --> 32:47.506
OUR INNOVATION
AND INSPIRATION OF SCIENTISTS

32:47.506 --> 32:49.508
LIKE DR. TORRES
AND MILLIONS OF OTHERS.

32:49.508 --> 32:52.301
IF WE HAVE A POLICY
THAT THWARTS INNOVATION,

32:52.301 --> 32:54.473
THEN WE'RE STOPPING
BEFORE WE EVEN START.

32:54.473 --> 32:57.686
IT'S A-A FUNDAMENTALLY
WRONG APPROACH,

32:57.686 --> 32:58.767
AND I CAN'T SUPPORT IT.

32:58.767 --> 33:01.020
OKAY.

33:01.020 --> 33:03.192
WE ARE WILLING TO SHARE
OUR SENSORS WITH YOU

33:03.192 --> 33:05.694
BUT ONLY IF
OUR WORK CONTINUES --

33:05.694 --> 33:08.107
IF EVERYBODY'S RESEARCH
CONTINUES.

33:08.107 --> 33:11.740
DR. SHEPHERD,
YOUR CONTRACT IS VERY CLEAR.

33:11.740 --> 33:15.074
WE HAVE SOLE RIGHT TO
YOUR SENSORS, OR YOU ARE OUT.

33:15.074 --> 33:16.705
THEN I AM OUT.

33:16.705 --> 33:19.078
THE PRESIDENT HIMSELF --

33:19.078 --> 33:20.289
YOU CAN TELL THAT
TO THE PRESIDENT.

33:20.289 --> 33:21.710
BETTER YET,
GET HIM ON THE PHONE.

33:21.710 --> 33:22.921
I WILL TELL HIM MYSELF.

33:22.921 --> 33:25.674
EITHER THE POLICY GOES,
OR I GO.

33:25.674 --> 33:31.720
WE WILL...HAVE TO...
FIGURE OUT...

33:31.720 --> 33:34.303
A...WAY TO SHARE.

33:34.303 --> 33:40.139
IN THE MEANTIME, YOU CAN SEND
US THE PLANS FOR YOUR SENSORS,

33:40.139 --> 33:43.602
AND, UH, DR. TORRES, OF COURSE,
UH, SHOULD CONTINUE HER WORK.

33:43.602 --> 33:48.817
THANK YOU...UH, LLOYD,
FOR YOUR COOPERATION.

33:48.817 --> 33:50.239
I'LL TALK TO YOU SOON.
WHOO-HOO-HOO-HOO-HOO!

33:50.239 --> 33:52.281
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
YES! UNH!

33:56.115 --> 33:58.117
GREG. JODI.

33:58.117 --> 34:00.289
OKAY, EVERYTHING
WENT VERY WELL.

34:00.289 --> 34:02.331
WE'RE GOING --
YOU PROMISED ME.

34:02.331 --> 34:04.333
COUGH IT UP.
MURPHY.

34:09.298 --> 34:10.299
THANK YOU.

34:13.802 --> 34:17.266
OH, MY GOD!
THAT'S HORRIBLE!

34:17.266 --> 34:18.517
THANK YOU FOR TAKING THAT
OUT OF ME.

34:18.517 --> 34:20.389
TAKE THAT AWAY.
TAKE THAT AWAY.

34:20.389 --> 34:21.770
THANK YOU. OHH.

34:21.770 --> 34:25.184
OH. OHH. OH.

34:25.184 --> 34:26.355
YOU STUPID IDIOT.

34:26.355 --> 34:28.777
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:28.777 --> 34:30.779
YOU WANT ME TO TAKE THAT
BACK TO PATH?

34:30.779 --> 34:33.192
OH, ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
THIS IS MY BIRTHDAY PRESENT.

34:33.192 --> 34:34.243
OHH.

34:34.243 --> 34:36.865
UH, SPEAKING OF WHICH,
I'LL SEE YOU, WHAT,

34:36.865 --> 34:39.328
IN ABOUT,
UH...HALF AN HOUR?

34:39.328 --> 34:40.539
SIR?

34:40.539 --> 34:42.541
OKAY, NOW YOU'RE
MAKING ME FEEL BAD.

34:42.541 --> 34:45.624
W-WHAT -- IF I'D HAVE KNOWN
YOU WANTED A PARTY,

34:45.624 --> 34:48.547
I WOULD HAVE -- LOOK, UH,
COME TO DINNER WITH ME AND BEN.

34:48.547 --> 34:51.380
OH, OH, PLEASE. PLEASE,
WE'D LOVE TO -- WE'D LOVE T--

34:51.380 --> 34:52.341
UH, B-BAILEY, STOP.
BAILEY.

34:52.341 --> 34:54.633
[ Chuckling ] BAILEY,
I WAS JUST JOKING.

34:54.633 --> 34:56.385
[ SIGHS ]

34:56.385 --> 34:59.017
GO AND HAVE FUN.

34:59.017 --> 35:01.810
S...

35:01.810 --> 35:04.183
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

35:04.183 --> 35:06.355
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

35:06.355 --> 35:07.776
NO, IT'S GOOD.

35:07.776 --> 35:09.228
[ DOOR OPENS ]

35:09.228 --> 35:10.359
EDWARDS.

35:10.359 --> 35:12.991
[ GASPS ] OH.
YOU HAD ONE JOB.

35:12.991 --> 35:15.654
DR. GREY, WE WERE JUST,
UH, LOOKING AT ERIC'S DESIGNS,

35:15.654 --> 35:17.035
WHICH ARE ACTUALLY
KIND OF AMAZING.

35:17.035 --> 35:18.947
I'M FIRED.
I'M TOTALLY FIRED.
LISTEN, GARY.

35:18.947 --> 35:21.160
UH, ERIC.
WHAT-- WHATEVER.

35:21.160 --> 35:22.371
THIS WAS
MY MOTHER'S PROJECT.

35:22.371 --> 35:23.742
I TOOK IT OVER.
IT'S MY PROJECT.

35:23.742 --> 35:25.204
SO, IT'S SORT OF LIKE
MY FAMILY HEIRLOOM.

35:25.204 --> 35:26.795
I TOTALLY GET IT.
I HAVE THIS TEACUP --

35:26.795 --> 35:28.747
IT'S MY BABY,
AND I FAILED IT.

35:28.747 --> 35:30.339
NO, YOU DIDN'T.
STOP TALKING.

35:30.339 --> 35:32.251
I FAILED IT,
AND THAT'S NOT OKAY

35:32.251 --> 35:34.423
BECAUSE OTHER PEOPLE'S
BABIES ARE GROWING.

35:34.423 --> 35:36.425
THEY'RE THRIVING.
THEY'RE SAVING LIVES.

35:36.425 --> 35:38.307
THEY'RE GETTING PATS
ON THE BACKS FROM PRESIDENTS.

35:38.307 --> 35:40.389
AND MINE IS SITTING
IN A BASEMENT,

35:40.389 --> 35:41.850
AND WE NEED
TO CHANGE THAT.

35:41.850 --> 35:43.222
SHE SAID "WE."
YEAH, IT'S A GOOD SIGN.

35:43.222 --> 35:44.603
HAVE A SEAT.

35:44.603 --> 35:45.764
BEFORE YOU START PRINTING,

35:45.764 --> 35:47.816
I WANT TO GO OVER
A FEW THINGS WITH YOU.

35:47.816 --> 35:50.189
WELL,
I'M GOOD RIGHT HERE.
I SAID "SIT."

35:50.189 --> 35:54.403
SO, THE FIRST TIME WE PRINTED,
I THINK WHERE I WENT WRONG IS...

35:54.403 --> 35:57.035
♪ MY FRIENDS WONDER
WHY I CALL YOU ♪
Sheryll: [ SIGHS ]
SHE'S SO BEAUTIFUL.

35:57.035 --> 35:58.447
♪ ALL THE TIME ♪
[ SNIFFLES ]

35:58.447 --> 35:59.488
♪ WHAT CAN I SAY? ♪
YOU'RE TELLING ME
SHE'S GONNA

35:59.488 --> 36:01.119
HAVE TO GROW UP
WITHOUT A MOTHER?

36:01.119 --> 36:03.332
THERE ARE
OTHER OPTIONS.

36:03.332 --> 36:06.335
♪ I DON'T
FEEL THE NEED TO GIVE ♪
YOU CAN GET
ON A TRANSPLANT LIST.

36:06.335 --> 36:07.546
♪ SUCH SECRETS AWAY ♪
AND MAYBE
THE NEXT PHASE OF TRIALS

36:07.546 --> 36:08.747
WILL BE MORE INCLUSIVE.

36:08.747 --> 36:09.958
BUT I WANT THIS ONE.

36:09.958 --> 36:11.550
♪ YOU THINK
THAT MAYBE I NEED HELP ♪

36:11.550 --> 36:15.384
♪ NO, I KNOW I'M RIGHT ♪
I AM SO, SO SORRY.

36:15.384 --> 36:16.385
♪ ALL RIGHT ♪

36:16.385 --> 36:17.756
YOU DON'T
MEET THE CRITERIA.

36:17.756 --> 36:21.720
♪ I'M JUST BETTER OFF NOT
LISTENING TO FRIENDS' ADVICE ♪

36:21.720 --> 36:23.302
CALL YOUR MOM.
[ SNIFFLES ]

36:23.302 --> 36:25.514
♪ AND WHEN THEY INSIST
ON KNOWING MY BLISS ♪
[ BABY COOS ]

36:25.514 --> 36:28.687
I BET
SHE'S WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

36:28.687 --> 36:32.271
♪ MM, OH, I TELL THEM THIS ♪

36:32.271 --> 36:36.485
♪ WHEN THEY WANT TO KNOW
WHAT THE REASON IS ♪

36:36.485 --> 36:40.579
♪ I ONLY SMILE WHEN I LIE
AND I TELL THEM WHY ♪

36:40.579 --> 36:44.413
♪ BECAUSE YOUR KISS,
YOUR KISS IS ON MY LIPS ♪

36:44.413 --> 36:45.584
♪ 'CAUSE YOUR KISS,
YOUR KISS I CAN'T RESIST ♪

36:45.584 --> 36:48.587
HONESTLY,
I'M REALLY PROUD OF MY BOY.

36:48.587 --> 36:53.001
HE HAD THE STONES TO STAND UP
AND ASK FOR TRUE LOVE.

36:53.001 --> 36:55.594
I -- THAT'S SCARY.

36:55.594 --> 36:57.796
OF COURSE,
I WOULD NEVER TELL HIM THAT.

36:57.796 --> 37:00.799
MM-HMM.

37:00.799 --> 37:03.221
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

37:03.221 --> 37:05.394
YOU WERE QUIET
ALL THE WAY HERE.

37:05.394 --> 37:07.806
ARE YOU SAD BECAUSE NO ONE
CELEBRATED YOUR BIRTHDAY?

37:07.806 --> 37:11.350
OH, COME ON.
I'M NOT A CHILD.

37:11.350 --> 37:14.313
HUNT'S TRYING TO PUSH ME
INTO RETIREMENT.
WHAT?

37:14.313 --> 37:17.195
HE STARTED THE DAY BY HANDING ME
DIRECTIONS TO THE PASTURE.

37:17.195 --> 37:19.568
AND YOU TOLD HIM
WHERE TO STICK IT, RIGHT?

37:19.568 --> 37:22.361
OH, COME ON.

37:22.361 --> 37:24.202
DON'T SLOW DOWN
ON ME NOW.

37:24.202 --> 37:26.415
I'M READY TO START
THE NEXT PART OF MY LIFE.

37:26.415 --> 37:28.577
AND I THOUGHT
I WAS GONNA DO IT WITH YOU.

37:28.577 --> 37:30.579
IF YOU'RE NOT UP FOR IT,
YOU'D BETTER STEP ASIDE.

37:30.579 --> 37:32.371
AND IF YOU ARE,
YOU -- MM.

37:32.371 --> 37:33.672
♪ DID THE NIGHT
JUST TAKE UP YOUR TIME? ♪

37:33.672 --> 37:38.086
♪ 'CAUSE IT MEANS MORE TO ME ♪
[ SIGHS ]

37:38.086 --> 37:40.469
♪ SOMETIMES I FORGET
WHAT I'M DOING ♪

37:40.469 --> 37:41.720
LET'S GO.

37:41.720 --> 37:43.592
ALL RIGHT.

37:43.592 --> 37:45.013
NOW SMILE.

37:45.013 --> 37:46.224
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:46.224 --> 37:47.436
AND ACT SURPRISED.

37:47.436 --> 37:49.348
WHAT?
MM.

37:49.348 --> 37:52.060
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

37:52.060 --> 37:53.602
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

37:53.602 --> 37:55.484
[ LAUGHS ]

37:57.396 --> 37:59.157
SURPRISE.

38:07.326 --> 38:09.287
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, SIR.

38:09.287 --> 38:12.250
YOU LOOKED RIGHT IN MY EYES,
AND YOU LIED TO ME, BAILEY.

38:12.250 --> 38:14.212
YEAH, BUT IT DIDN'T COUNT
BECAUSE YOU WERE BEING STUPID.

38:14.212 --> 38:15.834
[ LAUGHTER ]

38:15.834 --> 38:18.216
Derek: HEY.
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

38:18.216 --> 38:20.258
WELL, THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

38:20.258 --> 38:22.631
HEY, ARIZONA TOLD ME
THAT JACKSON PUT TOGETHER

38:22.631 --> 38:25.053
A COMMITTEE TO LOOK INTO
THIS THING FOR YOU AND CALLIE.

38:25.053 --> 38:26.635
OH, WE SHOULD --
MY GOD. WHOOPS.
YOU CAN TELL HIM TO STOP.

38:26.635 --> 38:29.638
YOU NEED A DRINK?
[ Chuckling ] YEAH.

38:29.638 --> 38:31.600
YOU CAN HAVE A DRINK.
WAIT, WELL --
WELL, WHAT HAPPENED?

38:31.600 --> 38:33.231
WE OVERTHREW THE GOVERNMENT
TODAY. WE'RE THIRSTY.

38:33.231 --> 38:36.234
I DON'T -- WHAT?

38:36.234 --> 38:37.896
♪ I DON'T FEEL THE NEED
TO GIVE SUCH SECRETS AWAY ♪

38:37.896 --> 38:40.699
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

38:40.699 --> 38:42.320
OKAY. [ SIGHS ]
HERE'S YOUR DRINK.

38:42.320 --> 38:43.492
I'LL BE BETTER
ONCE I'VE HAD THIS.

38:43.492 --> 38:46.324
♪ YOU THINK
THAT MAYBE I NEED HELP ♪

38:46.324 --> 38:47.325
HERE YOU GO.

38:47.325 --> 38:48.747
♪ I KNOW THAT I'M RIGHT ♪

38:48.747 --> 38:50.288
WOMEN LOVE YOU.

38:50.288 --> 38:53.291
YOU'VE HAD
OVER 20 RESPONSES.

38:53.291 --> 38:54.453
I NARROWED IT DOWN
TO 10.

38:54.453 --> 38:57.215
YOU SHOULD LOOK THESE OVER.
PICK THREE FOR COFFEE DATES.

38:57.215 --> 38:59.418
HMM.
[ SIGHS ]

38:59.418 --> 39:01.169
HMM.
MM-HMM.

39:01.169 --> 39:05.343
OKAY, I GOT TO GO TALK
TO WEBBER, AND, AFTER THAT,

39:05.343 --> 39:07.265
I THINK WE SHOULD
GET OUT OF HERE.

39:07.265 --> 39:09.347
OWEN.
YOU COULD JUST WAIT HERE.

39:09.347 --> 39:12.431
OR WE COULD MEET BACK
AT YOUR PLACE.

39:12.431 --> 39:14.933
OWEN.
MM-HMM?

39:14.933 --> 39:18.527
♪ 'CAUSE YOUR KISS,
YOUR KISS IS ON MY LIST ♪

39:18.527 --> 39:21.740
♪ BECAUSE YOUR KISS,
YOUR KISS I CAN'T RESIST ♪

39:21.740 --> 39:22.941
♪ BECAUSE YOUR KISS
IS ON MY LIST ♪

39:22.941 --> 39:24.322
SEE?

39:24.322 --> 39:28.326
I CAN GET IN TROUBLE FOR THAT,
AND I DON'T WANT TO.

39:28.326 --> 39:31.119
THIS ISN'T A PROMISE
OF ANYTHING.
[ SIGHS ]

39:31.119 --> 39:33.331
YOU WANT A PROMISE?
I CAN PROMISE YOU THIS --

39:33.331 --> 39:35.954
YOU CAN'T COUNT ON ME,
'CAUSE STUFF HAPPENS, YOU KNOW?

39:35.954 --> 39:38.587
HOUSES BURN. CARS CRASH.
PEOPLE GET SICK.

39:38.587 --> 39:40.589
ONE OF US
COULD DIE TOMORROW.

39:40.589 --> 39:43.001
I PROMISE YOU
CANNOT COUNT ON ANYTHING,

39:43.001 --> 39:45.964
BUT THIS MAKES IT SO...I CAN
KISS YOU WHENEVER I WANT TO.

39:45.964 --> 39:49.347
I DON'T WANT THE STUPID
RUNNING AROUND AND HIDING.

39:49.347 --> 39:50.719
I WANT TO KISS YOU
WHEN I WANT TO KISS YOU.

39:50.719 --> 39:52.350
[ PEN CLICKS ]

39:52.350 --> 39:55.313
WHAT CAN I GET FOR YOU?

39:55.313 --> 40:00.108
♪ I GO CRAZY WONDERING
WHAT THERE IS TO REALLY SEE ♪

40:00.108 --> 40:03.111
YES.
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:03.111 --> 40:06.324
♪ DID THE NIGHT
JUST TAKE UP YOUR TIME? ♪

40:06.324 --> 40:09.658
♪ 'CAUSE IT MEANS MORE TO ME ♪

40:09.658 --> 40:12.290
I KNOW.

40:12.290 --> 40:13.702
KNOW WHAT?

40:13.702 --> 40:16.244
WHAT RELIGIOUS TRADITION
I WANT TO BRING MY KIDS UP IN.

40:16.244 --> 40:20.459
YOU SAID YOU DON'T --
YOU DON'T KNOW, BUT I DO.

40:20.459 --> 40:23.462
IT'S IMPORTANT TO ME
THAT THEY'RE CHRISTIAN.

40:23.462 --> 40:25.544
I THOUGHT YOU KNEW THAT.

40:25.544 --> 40:27.546
THAT MY KIDS WOULD HAVE
DIFFERENT BELIEFS THAN I DO?

40:27.546 --> 40:30.388
THAT'S --
THAT'S A LITTLE WEIRD, APRIL.

40:30.388 --> 40:32.260
TRANSITION IS MOVEMENT

40:32.260 --> 40:34.853
FROM ONE PART OF A LIFE
TO A WHOLE NEW ONE.

40:34.853 --> 40:38.316
A-A-AND
BOARD MEETINGS AT 15?

40:38.316 --> 40:41.319
I KIND OF PICTURED
MY KIDS IN 4-H.

40:41.319 --> 40:43.361
LIKE RAISING PIGS?

40:43.361 --> 40:45.564
OR COWS.

40:45.564 --> 40:48.406
